UID:01vd9ltqg3f7dkd25qav8ci84k@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:On Saturday\, February 23rd\, National Electronics Museum (NEM)
  will be holding it's 4th Annual Techno-Swap-Fest. The Unallocated Space (U
 AS) invites you to join us and bring hobbyist\, family\, and friends togeth
 er to show off your techie spirit. This is a perfect opportunity to meet pe
 ople with similar interest\, find what your looking for\, trade up\, trade 
 down\, or donate what you don't need. All entrance proceeds support the Nat
 ional Electronics. Adults $5\, Kids under 16 FREE.\n\nThe UAS is a club spo
 nsor and will be attending this event. Don't forget to visit us! We will be
  more then happy to tell you about the exciting things we do. We will be ba
 rtering\, selling and accepting donates at this event\, as well be entering
  in a contest for the most unusual\, least useful\, best dust collector ite
 m\, so come out and see what it is. Vote for us!\n\n*** During Swap Fest\, 
 the NEM will be running a workshop to build your own LED Moon Globe. This q
 uick and easy project is perfect for kids and adults alike. No registration
  is needed. A limited number of kits are available for purchase\, so come e
 arly.\n\n====\n\nAttention All Hobbyists\n\n* Is your shop so cluttered you
  can barely work on your projects?\n* Did you buy something online that did
 n't fit into your plans?\n* Are you still looking for that perfect gadget\,
  part or tool?\n\nIf you answered YES or NO to any of these questions\, you
  need to attend the 4th Annual Techno-Swap-Fest to buy\, sell and gawk at a
 ll the precious junk that other hobbyists crave.\n\nHere are just some of t
 he hobbies represented last year at the Techno-Swap-Fest:\n\n* R/C (boats\,
  planes\, tanks\, cars\, trains\, geese\, monsters)\n* Robotics (competitio
 n\, combat\, R2D2\, micro-bots\, junk-bots)\n* Electronics (hackers\, maker
 s\, crackers\, phreaks\, HAMS)\n* Mechanical (steam engines\, CNC\, animatr
 onics\, whimsical)\n\nAnd some of the precious stuff (a.k.a. junk) you'll f
 ind:\n\n* motors\, gears\, tools\, parts\, radios\, televisions\, monitors\
 n* batteries\, materials\, wheels\, circuits\, gadgets\, cases\, plans\n* c
 omplete projects\, never-completed projects\, computers\n* electronic music
 al instruments\, lights\, models\, books\n* wearable electronics\, and much
 \, much more\n\nMore Reading...\n\nhttps://sites.google.com/site/technoswap
 fest2/\nhttps://sites.google.com/site/technoswapfest2/sponsors
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:National Electronics Museum   1745 West Nursery Road\, Linthicum M
 D
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Techno-Swap Fest - Join Unallocated Space!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
