UID:06elqflnb30g838b8u2q3ejapc@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Unallocated will be hosting the Central Maryland Software Defin
 ed Radio Meetup\n\nMeeting to discuss projects. If no one has a project I p
 lan to show the San Francisco SDR Project Meetup projects available online 
 to view via Utube\, they are super interesting! We're still looking for spe
 akers! Please get in touch if you'd like to present. \nOur lineup:\n\n• Nic
 k Foster @bistromath Satellite communications with GNU Radio\, SDR hardware
 \, homebrew antennas and satellite tracking.\n\n• Josh Myer @xek\n\nA coupl
 e months back\, some friends and I captured a bunch of RF telemetry from a 
 rocket launch down at Vandenburg AFB\, down by LA. I'll talk about how we d
 ecided what to capture\, what we captured\, and how we analyzed the many\, 
 many gigabytes of RF that wound up on a hard disk that morning.\n\n• Jonath
 on Pendlum @SDRJon\n\nRFNoC (RF Network on Chip)\, a new framework for Ettu
 s third generation devices (X300 & E300) that aims to make FPGA acceleratio
 n in SDRs more easily accessible. I will cover some background on FPGAs and
  their use in SDR\, the motivation and design of RFNoC\, and conclude with 
 a few live demos.\n\nThe Noisebridge wiki entry:\n\nhttps://noisebridge.net
 /wiki/Cyberspectrum\n\nhttps://www.meetup.com/CentralMDSDR/events/241597782
 /
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court 105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Central Maryland SDR - Project Discussions/SDR Techie
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
