DESCRIPTION:We will be mostly playing with using analog to control digital 
 LEDs.\n\nAgenda:\n\n1. Reading analog values from a potentiometer (variable
  resistor)\n2. Fading an LED using a potentiometer\n3. Controlling the rate
  of LED blinking using a potentiometer\n4. Using tactile switches to turn a
 n LED on and off\n\nRequired Items:\n\n1. Laptop\n2. Arduino\n3. USB cable 
 for your Arduino\n4. Breadboard\n5. Jumpers for breadboard\nProvided Items\
 n\n1. LEDs\n2. Potentiometers\n\nIf you need any items in the required item
 s section\, please E-Mail uas.arduino@gmail.com.  We have a few of all of t
 he required items\, but we need to know how many to prepare.\nSince the spa
 ce runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended do
 nation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance t
 o the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
