CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Prior to the meeting I would like everyone to go over the follo
 wing resources\n\nFor those unfamiliar with SQL\nhttp://sqlzoo.net/wiki/Mai
 n_Page\n\nJoe McCray's Defcon talk on Advanced SQL Injection. Warning\, he 
 does swear.\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-AkUutmXwUI\n\nOWASP SQL Injec
 tion Guides\nhttps://www.owasp.org/index.php/SQL_Injection\nhttps://www.owa
 sp.org/index.php/Blind_SQL_Injection\nhttps://www.owasp.org/index.php/Testi
 ng_for_SQL_Injection_(OWASP-DV-005)\n\nGo over the material a couple of tim
 es\, take notes\, write down\nquestions. I can suggest a bucket load of mor
 e resources if people\nwould like.\n\nAt the beginning of the meeting\, I'l
 l quickly go over the main points\nand fill in some gaps.\n\nThe bulk of th
 e meeting we'll be participating in the 2nd SQLiLab CTF\nhttp://ctf.notsose
 cure.com/\n\nThis will be more of a mentor/tutor session then a competition
 .\n\nI would like people experienced with SQL injection to volunteer as\nme
 ntors\, and be willing to present how to use various tools such as:\n - sql
 map\n - TheMole\n - w3af\n - zap\n - burpsuite\n - webinspect\n - some new 
 hotness you think everyone should use\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CTF Meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
