DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20160916T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:1has8v3quu8s869mab6km4lipg@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20160916T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Would you like to learn more about these little development boa
 rds that are popping up everywhere?  Arduino\, Raspberry Pi\, and Beaglebon
 e are some of the most popular boards out there.  Come out on Friday Nights
  to learn more about them.\n\nThis isn't just a simple install of the board
  and operating system.  Learn how to use sensors and make webservers to ser
 ve up all that data! If you've already learned about Arduino\, How about us
 ing your Pi or Bone to control multiple Arduinos to automate your whole hou
 se??\n\nGotta particular project in mind?  Bring it to the class and we can
  ALL learn from it!\n\nOur First Meeting will be Friday September 16th from
  7-10 pm.\nThen come back every 1st and 3rd Friday for more Microcontroller
  fun!\n\nIt is recommended that everyone got a PI 3\, Arduino\, and PI Sens
 or Hat for this series.\n \nWeek 1 Agenda\n--------------------------------
 \n1)   Basic Configuration  ( 1 hour)\n\n2)   Basic Configurations (zero\, 
 screens\, etc.) (30 minutes or so)\n\n3)   Discussions on what people want 
 to learn how to do. (30 minutes or so)\n\n4)   Basic sensor hat usage.  (In
 troduction to HW Interface.) (30 minutes or so)
