DESCRIPTION:Topics:\n - Introduction to Asterisk - history and versioning\n
  - Telephony - short discussion on different telephony methods used by aste
 risk\n - Installation / Main configuration files for Asterisk\n - Dialplan 
 and common dialplan configurations\n - Setting up a soft phone\n - Basic Tr
 oubleshooting\n - Summary\n\nWhat to bring:\n\n - Laptop\n - IP phone if yo
 u have one\, if not\, no worries we have a few loaners\n - Brain food! Snac
 ks\, etc.\n\nPre-reqs:\n\n - Basic understanding of Linux\n - how to use VI
 M/VI command line editors\n(the class will be mostly looking at the command
  line\, so if you are a little familiar it will be less painful)
