BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20150515T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20150515T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:1i68m7n28c7b89n27657pu5q68@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150515T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Last time we covered basic transistors.  Just turning an LED on
  and off and driving a DC motor.  This time we will look at creating an H b
 ridge to drive a DC motor forwards and backwards.  We will also be going a 
 little more in depth about transistors.\n\nFeel free to bring your own DC m
 otor.  We have a small collection of motors at the space.  Also bring a mul
 ti meter if you have one.  It's nice to be able to check the current draw t
 o make sure there are no shorts.\n\nIt is suggested to bring a full sized b
 read board since this will take up a little bit of room!\n\nAgenda:\n     1
 . Review of transistors\n     2. Functional difference between PNP and NPN\
 n     3. Explanation of an H bridge\n     4. Review datasheets\n     5. Wir
 e up the H bridge\n     6. Write a little code\n     7. Drive a DC motor wi
 th a 9 volt battery\n\n     \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E-
 Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to the Google Hangout
 .  The hangout will generally be started just before class (6:45-7:15 PM). 
  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, please E-Mail arduino@unallocatedsp
 ace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can be found a
 t https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=s
 haring.  The slides are generally made during the three days before a class
 .\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Me
 ga\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board does not have US
 B programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, 
 Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the 
 long one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are okay for now)\n
      4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop with the
  Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for
  your breadboard\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Transistors (4 NPN and 2 PNP
 ) (part number TBD)\n     2. DC motor\n     3. 4 Diodes\n     4. 9 Volt bat
 tery\n     5. Alligator clips (for the battery)\n     \n\nSince Unallocated
  Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommende
 d donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it d
 oes help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\,
  is 100% free to all!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
