BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20150605T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20150605T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:1i68m7n28c7b89n27657pu5q68@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150605T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Continuing the trend of motor control and transistors\, we will
  be driving bipolar steppers motors.  The motors will be provided since hav
 ing varying stepper motors can be troublesome.\n\nIt is suggested to bring 
 a full sized bread board since this will take up a little bit of room!\n\nA
 genda:\n     1. What is a stepper motor\n     2. Uses of stepper motors\n  
    3. How do stepper motors work\n     4. Wire up using transistors\n     5
 . Write code to spin one direction\n     6. Modify the code to spin both di
 rections\n     7. Wire up using little driver boards  \n     \nIf you canno
 t attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask 
 to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will generally be started j
 ust before class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, pl
 ease E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming an
 d previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0
 BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made dur
 ing the three days before a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino b
 oard of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     
 2. If your board does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a p
 rogrammer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino
 \, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small sq
 uare-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or pr
 ogrammer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, 
 or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard (male-male and either fem
 ale-female or female-male) (these are provided if needed)\n\n\nProvided Ite
 ms:\n     1. 28BYJ-48 stepper motor\n     2. Simple darlington driver board
 \n     \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to
  mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no me
 ans a requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to 
 the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
