UID:1i68m7n28c7b89n27657pu5q68@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150619T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Continuing the trend of motor control and transistors\, we will
  be driving unipolar steppers motors.  The motors will be provided since ha
 ving varying stepper motors can be troublesome.\n\nIt is suggested to bring
  a full sized bread board since this will take up a little bit of room!\n\n
 Agenda:\n     1. What is a stepper motor\n     2. Uses of stepper motors\n 
     3. How do stepper motors work\n     4. Wire up using transistors\n     
 5. Write code to spin one direction\n     6. Modify the code to spin both d
 irections\n     7. Wire up using little driver boards  \n     \nIf you cann
 ot attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask
  to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will generally be started 
 just before class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, p
 lease E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming a
 nd previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=
 0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made du
 ring the three days before a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino 
 board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n    
  2. If your board does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a 
 programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduin
 o\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small s
 quare-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or p
 rogrammer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\,
  or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard (male-male and either fe
 male-female or female-male) (these are provided if needed)\n\n\nProvided It
 ems:\n     1. 28BYJ-48 stepper motor\n     2. Simple darlington driver boar
 d\n     \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like t
 o mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no m
 eans a requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to
  the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
