DESCRIPTION:This will be informal since it's a holiday.  I will be covering
  the use of the 4 wire resistive touch sensors that we recovered from all t
 he GPS units.  If you want to be able to use an LCD with your finger or a s
 tylus then stop by at 7 and learn how easy it can be :)\n\nRequirements: La
 ptop\, Arduino (UNO\, Due\, etc)\, breadboard\, jumpers\, and a USB cable f
 or your Arduino\n\nIf you want to play with Python and serial as well\, the
 n make sure you have Python installed along with pyserial.  Using these two
  we can plot where your finger or stylus is at on the panel!\n\nThis class 
 will be repeated next time (in the formal format) since I imagine some peop
 le will be leaving the area for the holiday.\n\n-Proto
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20150717T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20150717T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:1i68m7n28c7b89n27657pu5q68@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150717T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:This will be my last class for a while.  But don't fret\, someo
 ne else has graciously volunteered to pick the class up!  I'm sure it'll be
  nice to have someone new :D\n\nAnywho\, this class will focus on 4 wire re
 sistive touch screens.  These are attached to LCD screens from Garmin GPS u
 nits.\n\nPython will be required for the last part of this class.  Please e
 nsure that you have Python with pygame and pyserial installed prior to clas
 s!!  If you have issues installing either\, please contact arduino@unalloca
 tedspace.org.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. How do resistive touch screens work\n    
  2. Wire the screens up\n     3. Write code to determine position of stylus
 /finger\n     4. Use Python (with pyserial and pygame) to render position i
 nformation\n     \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduin
 o@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hang
 out will generally be started just before class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do 
 not have an invite by 7:15\, please E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\
 nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://d
 rive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  Th
 e slides are generally made during the three days before a class.\n\nRequir
 ed Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boardu
 ino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board does not have USB programmi
 ng built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster
 \, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if
  possible\, though the small square-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB
  cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino ID
 E installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Python with pygame and pyse
 rial installed\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. 4 wire resistive touch panel\n
      \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to m
 ention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no mean
 s a requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to th
 e space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
