DESCRIPTION:Arduino Class (7PM - ?)\n\nTopics:\n     Driving LEDs with tran
 sistors (we have 2N2222 transistors at the space)\n     Driving inductive l
 oads with transistors (we will be providing DC motors and batteries)\n     
 Buttons (buttons will be provided.  will also cover debouncing with hardwar
 e and software)\n     7 segment displays (will be provided)\n     Interfaci
 ng with Static Random Access Memory (approx 5 chips will be provided)\n\nRe
 quirements:\n     Arduino (any kind will do)\n     Laptop (there are some a
 t the space if needed\, but they are slow)\n     Full size breadboard (only
  2-3 will be provided)\n     USB cable (whatever type is used for your Arud
 ino)\n\nIf you would like to participate\, but do not have any of the requi
 red items\, please let me know.  I have a few extras of everything\, but I 
 need to know ahead of time!\n\nBig thanks to Bowie for the box of 2\,000 tr
 ansistors!  Those are the ones we will be using on Friday.\n\nIf enough peo
 ple bring 2x16 character LCD displays then I will walk everyone through set
 ting those up!  I wish I could teach it anyway\, but I only have one or two
  of em.\n\nPlease let me know if you plan to attend.  It's by no means a re
 quirement.  It just serves to give me an idea of how many people to prepare
  for.\n\nFeel free to bring things that you want to use the Arduino to inte
 rface with.  Think of it as show and tell :)
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
