BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20121222T000000Z
DTEND:20121222T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:33ef410pmaapeeoilhmg99v73g@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Back by popular demand!  Please make note of the fact that the 
 time is back to the normal 7 PM instead of 6 PM.\n\nAgenda:\n1. Transistors
  for LEDs and motors (a repeat\, but really important!)\n2. Shift registers
  to control LEDs (and possibly 7 segment displays)\n3. Using tactile switch
 es (including de-bouncing)\n4. Talking to other Arduinos \n\n(I do not expe
 ct to get to number 4\, but it's there if we do!)\n\n\nRequired Items:\n1. 
 Breadboard (please let me know if you need one as I have several to borrow)
 \n2. Arduino (any kind will work\, including the DIY builds)\n3. Laptop (pl
 ease let me know if you need one as the space has about 3)\n4. Jumper wires
 \n5. 9 volt battery (for the transistor portion)\n\n\nProvided Items:\n1. L
 EDs (red/green and single color)\n2. 7 segment display (mix of common catho
 de and common anode)\n3. Shift register (74HC595)\n4. Tactile switch\n5. 2N
 2222A transistor\n\nIf you would like a shift register of your own\, please
  let me know.  I ordered 10 for the last class and will happily part with t
 hem for a $1 donation to the space.  For those of you who would like to ord
 er one prior to the class\, the part number is 74HC595.  Available from Jam
 eco\, Mouser\, DigiKey\, Adafruit\, and SparkFun.  I am fairly certain that
  we have several at the space as well.\n\nSince the space runs off of donat
 ions\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this clas
 s is $10.  It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space and th
 is class is\, as usual\, 100% free to all!  And a huge thank you to those o
 f you who donated last time!\n\nFor questions/comments\, please contact uas
 .arduino@gmail.com.\n\nHope to see you all there :)\n\nOh\, and here are so
 me links for the "Available from Jameco\, Mouser\, DigiKey\, Adafruit\, and
  SparkFun" part:\n\nhttp://www.jameco.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/Product
 _10001_10001_46105_-1\nhttp://www.mouser.com/ProductDetail/NXP-Semiconducto
 rs/74HC595N112/?qs=sGAEpiMZZMvKM5ialpXrmr5J3bDXowCz\nhttp://www.digikey.com
 /product-detail/en/SN74HC595N/296-1600-5-ND/277246\nhttps://www.adafruit.co
 m/products/450\nhttps://www.sparkfun.com/products/733
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
