DESCRIPTION:Purpose: \nThis is an interest and study group designed to help
  participants prepare for and pass the OSCP exam and generally develop thei
 r skills in pentesting. The goal is to share and improve.\n\nFormat:\n\nDur
 ing the previous week decide on a vulnerable VM\, download it into our pers
 onal labs and hack it over the course of the week. On OSCP Night\, we do a 
 screenshare and we work over it live and show how we hacked it. At the end 
 I toss the minutes and any scripts people made up onto the share. \n\nMore 
 recently we've got a working bed of vulnerable machines\, designed to simul
 ate the OSCP environment. \n\nNext Meetup: \nCheck the website for weekly u
 pdates:  http://www.unallocatedspace.org/uas/tag/oscp/ \n\nFor details abou
 t the exam: \nhttps://support.offensive-security.com/#!oscp-exam-guide.md
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:OSCP Study Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
