DESCRIPTION:4 Hour Git Workshop (preceding our UAS Hackathon)\n------------
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ----\nWe'll discover what Git is\, its relationship to Github\, and high le
 vel Git operation. We'll talk about situations where Git is and is not usef
 ul\, and its relationship to other version control systems. Also\, there wi
 ll be some discussion regarding the purpose of version control and the appl
 ication of continuous integration as a part of the development lifecycle. W
 e'll talk about Github and its relationship to the mission of Unallocated S
 pace.\n\nWe will also cover deeper topics on Git. See the link for more inf
 o: http://unallocated.github.io/hackathon/gitworkshop/
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, United 
 States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Git Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
