UID:4aq9fddjhcjpfgnr18i2ev7c48@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:All\,\n\nHow exciting does build a computer from scratch sound?
  \n\nWhether learning how to build your very own computer or just building 
 one in the company of others\, you will enjoy this (3 day / 8 hr) class. An
 d let’s not forget\, Valentine's Day is right around the corner\, so join u
 s at Unallocated Space (UAS) and learn how to build a computer from scratch
 . \n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that
  the recommended donation for this class is $10 a day. It is by no means a 
 requirement! Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all
 !\n\nv\\r\n\nBuddy\nTeach\, Learn\, Build (Party)\nhttp://www.unallocatedsp
 ace.org\n\n====\n\nEvent Details:\n\nTuesday\, February 5\, 2013 (7PM to 9P
 M)\n\nClass 1 / 2 hrs (Part 1) Hardware Basics - Building a computer from s
 cratch gives you the perfect machine for your needs\, but it can be dauntin
 g the first time around. For our first lesson in building your own PC\, we 
 start with a little computer hardware basics. -- (Part 2) Choose and Buy Yo
 ur Parts - In this lesson\, we'll show you how to most effectively pick out
  and shop for your parts. \n\nSaturday or Sunday (TBD by the Class)\n\nCass
  2 / 3 hrs (Optional) – Fieldtrip to Micro Center – Let’s be honest\, these
  classes are not complete until we do a fieldtrip to our local computer sup
 ply store. As determined by the class\, we will choose a day to carpool to 
 Micro Center (or another store of our choosing).\n\nTuesday\, February 12\,
  2013 (7PM to 10PM)\n\nClass 3 / 3 hrs (Part 1) Building the Computer - Ass
 embling your computer can seem daunting\, but it's actually pretty easy. In
  part 1\, we show you step-by-step how to put everything together. -- (Part
  2) Installing Your Operating System (e.g. Ubuntu http://www.ubuntu.com \,W
 indows\, etc.) - Once you've put it together\, you're past the difficult po
 rtion. With installing your operating system and get everything up and runn
 ing. -- (Part 3) Show Off & Further Resources - This night we will show off
  our creations and share any resources we discovered.\n\nLocation: Unalloca
 ted Space\nAddress:‎ 512 Shaw Court # 105\, Severn\, MD 21144\nhttp://www.u
 nallocatedspace.org/uas/about-us/\n\nAdapted from: \nhttp://lifehacker.com/
 5828747/how-to-build-a-computer-from-scratch-the-complete-guide
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space (Severn\, MD)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:How to Built a Computer from Scratch - Class 3
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20170810T230000Z
DTEND:20170811T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:4hr7tt4am4rdgijld8jmuq1sig@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:DATE: 10AUG2017\nTIME: 1900-2200\nTOPIC: INFOSEC NIGHT: Practic
 al Privacy with a slice of Pi\nSUMMARY:  \nOur privacy online has never bee
 n under more threat than it is today. With bulk data collection rampant\, a
 nd ISPs obtaining the right to sell browsing history how do you maintain a 
 practical level of privacy and take control of your digital life back.\n\nI
 n this talk we will discuss the different adversaries stalking you online\,
  the common problems with your private information and data leakage\, and h
 ow to protect your online presence in a practical manner on a sliding scale
  based on the level of impact and level of privacy that you are comfortable
  with.\n\nAre you concerned with being tracked by Google\, Facebook\, and t
 he like? You are not alone. Come to InfoSec Night\, learn about your advers
 aries\, and how to stay safe online. Bring a Raspberry Pi 3 and leave with 
 a Wireless Access Point that will make TOR accessible to you.\n\nGOAL:  \n\
 n1 Know your adversary and how to protect your privacy at a level of anonym
 ity that you are comfortable with.\n2 Build an AP that will use TOR to crea
 te another layer of privacy\n\nThings to bring:  Raspberry PI\, sd card\, p
 ower supply\, crossover cable\, case\n\nPis will be available on site in li
 mited supply for sale.\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone\nPRESENTER: httpLov3craft\
 n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC NIGHT: Practical Privacy with a slice of Pi
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
