UID:5gcqpfa34pk89tpuob3vmoq37c@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Unallocated Space Tuesday\, April 4th\, 2017 at 7pm
  to 10pm for an introduction to radio frequency (RF) signal analysis. This 
 4 week class will cover locating\, identifying\, demodulating\, and decodin
 g common RF signal types.\n\nWeek 1: We will make sure everybody’s system i
 s working. We will decode some basic signals just for test purposes. If you
  are sure your Linux system is working with the tools mentioned below you c
 an skip this session.\n\nWeek 2: We will cover the various modulation types
  and digital encoding schemes. This will include learning to listen for dig
 ital signals\, and visually identify them on the waterfall.\n\nWeek 3: We w
 ill practice decoding several different types of signals. We will also touc
 h on how to use the GNU Radio Companion.\n\nWeek 4: We will look at reverse
  engineering some FSK and ASK/OOK type signals. We will use different tools
  such as Baudline and Waveconverter\n\nPlease bring the following hardware 
 items:\n\n    An SDR capable of receiving between 50MHz and 1GHz (almost al
 l RTL-SDRs cover this range\, and any of the more expensive SDRs will cover
  this range as well\, except for the BladeRF)\n    An omni-directional ante
 nna\n    “Aux cable” (3.5mm “headphone” connector on both ends)\n    A fair
 ly powerful laptop or desktop (At least 2 cores clocked over 2GHz\, 4GB RAM
 ) Sorry\, that old laptop you got for $50 at the hamfest won’t cut it.\n\nP
 lease have the following software installed BEFORE class:\n\n    Your favor
 ite Linux distro on a dedicated partition. NO virtual machines! Linux begin
 ners\, please install Ubuntu.\n    Any drivers necessary to run your SDR\n 
    GNU Radio\n    GQRX\n    fldigi\n    QSSTV\n    pulse audio volume contr
 ol\n\nThere are resources for how to install all of the above software onli
 ne. Please have it installed before class\, the network cannot handle every
 one downloading that stuff all at once.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Signal Analysis with SDR
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
