DESCRIPTION:Unallocated Space\, a local Anne Arundel County Hackerspace in 
 Severn\, MD is excited to invite you\, your family\, and friends to its fir
 st community tech swap meet / garage sale on Saturday June 8th 2013 at elev
 en o'clock to six pm.\n\nThe purpose of the sale is to clear space and rais
 e money for future projects and serve as a way for the community to recycle
 .\n\nOur mission is to Teach\, Learn\, and Build! See the UAS’ blog post fo
 r more details\, including directions at www.unallocatedspace.org.\n\n WHAT
  WILL YOU FIND?\n\nAnything is possible. Things to expect to see for sale w
 ill vary\, but here are a few examples of what to expect.\n\n* misc. server
 s and computers equipment * misc. antiquated hardware * ethernet switches *
  sever racks * ham radios * capacitors * audio equipment * peripherals * ca
 meras / microscopes * wifi equipment * lights * extension cords!! * mouse (
 mice) * mystery box! * UPS * old and new TVs * high voltage power supplies 
 * tools * game systems * electrical equipment * etc.\n\nSELL YOUR STUFF!\n\
 n For those considering setting up a table or taking a space at this commun
 ity event\, we are asking for a $5 dollars donation and welcome any other d
 onations (cash or items). We will have tables for you to use\, but space wi
 ll be limited (first come\, first serve)\, but you are welcome to bring you
 r own table.\n\nMembers and participants are encouraged to park in the back
  near the garage.\n\nPLEASE SHARE!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Unallocated Space 512 Shaw Ct #105 Severn\, Ma
 ryland 21144
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Unallocated Space (UAS) Community Tech Swap Meet/Garage Sale (Anne 
 Arundel\, MD)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
