DESCRIPTION:Holly Area of Greenbelt Park\, we will be setting up for ARRL F
 ield Day (http://www.arrl.org/field-day). Field Day is setup to create conn
 ections and foster communication to as many other stations as possible. We 
 are working towards having a completely self-powered site with multiple tra
 nsmission stations. It can be a lot of fun to see what states/countries you
  can talk to at different hours. We have a group that will be camping nearb
 y during the event.  \n\nSetup and Teardown will occur before and after the
  2pm to 2pm window.  Regardless if you have your HAM radio license or not\,
  we would love to have you come out and get on the air. \n\n\n\nObjective- 
 \nTo work as many stations as possible on any and all amateur bands (exclud
 ing the 60\, 30\, 17\, and 12-meter bands) and to learn to operate in abnor
 mal situations in less than optimal conditions. Field Day is open to all am
 ateurs in the areas covered by the ARRL/RAC Field Organizations and countri
 es within IARU Region 2. DX stations residing in other regions may be conta
 cted for credit\, but are not eligible to submit entries.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Greenbelt Park\, Holly Area\, 6565 Greenbelt Road\, Greenbelt\, MD
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Field Day
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
