DESCRIPTION:**You’re invited to the Unallocated Space’s Seventh Year Annive
 rsary Party!\n\nThe time is upon us again. It's time to celebrate our succe
 sses with all our friends and patrons! Unallocated Space (UAS) cordially in
 vites everyone to join us on Saturday\, November 11\, 2017 to celebrating 7
  years of providing the community a place to teach\, learn\, and build.\n\n
 Expect copious amounts of food\, drink\, people\, and music. What would be 
 an UAS Party without a fire tornado ‽ (Interroban: U+203D) Thank goodness y
 ou don’t need to ponder this too long. There will be an epic fire tornado a
 nd mini conflagration (aka camp fire).\n\nAlso we are excited about updatin
 g you on the good things we’ve been up to and love to thank all those outst
 anding individuals who’ve contributed to the space this year by making a fe
 w exciting announcements and changes within UAS. **If you like having fun a
 nd meeting people with similar interests\, then this event is for you!\n\n+
  Date/Time: Saturday\, November 11\, 2017 / 3PM - 12AM \n+ Location: Unallo
 cated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct Ste 105\, Severn\, MD 21144\n\n**We will be condu
 cting a potluck and this is your opportunity to show off your culinary skil
 ls and fancy imported beer. Please help us by updating our Google Doc with 
 the food and drinks you’re bringing. http://goo.gl/KuqXLh\n\n**We look forw
 ard to seeing you there! \n\n**Please RSVP at https://www.meetup.com/Unallo
 cated-Space/events/241912360/ .\n\n===\n\nFrequently Asked Questions:\n\n+ 
 (Q) What is the scheduled activities? (A) \n- 3PM to 6PM - Table Flipping &
  50/50 Raffle \n- 3PM to 6PM - 3D Printing / Analog Board Games \n- 3PM - M
 idnight - Music\, Music\, Music!!! \n- 4PM - Food & Drinks \n- 6PM - Board 
 Announcements \n- 7PM - Winner Announcements \n- 8PM to 12AM - Fire Tornado
  & Camp-Style Fire\n\n\n+ (Q) Who is invited? (A) Everyone! Twitter: "RT @U
 nallocated (of Severn\, MD) is having its 7 Year Anniversary Party #hackers
 pace on Sat\, Nov 11\, 2017 RSVP https://www.meetup.com/Unallocated-Space/e
 vents/241912360" \n\n+ (Q) Who is UAS? (A) Unallocated Space is a 501(c)(3)
  Non-profit Hackerspace. Our mission is to foster creative and technical gr
 owth through open collaboration by providing tools and resources within the
  greater Baltimore-Washington Metro area. Learn more at http://www.unalloca
 tedspace.org .\n\n+ (Q) How to support to UAS? (A) Unlike most hackerspaces
 \, all of our events\, classes\, and workshops are completely open to the g
 eneral public for free. We have continued to serve the community in this ma
 nner for seven years. You can find m
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
