DESCRIPTION:We started work on our CPU last week.  This class will focus on
  getting the CPU up and running with simple instructions like add\, subtrac
 t\, multiply\, divide\, jump\, and sending data to the IO ports.\n\nRequire
 d Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensure you already h
 ave the ISE installed!!  We will not have time to wait for the install proc
 ess to complete (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xil
 inx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-to
 ols.html and download the ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spa
 rtan 3 or greater FPGA development board (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer the
  Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev board.\n\nWe ar
 e to a point in the class where anyone wishing to join will need to E-Mail 
 fpga@unallocatedspace.org.  The reason being that we will need to verify th
 at you know VHDL well\, and have a development board already.\n\nBecause of
  the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we will not have extras.  If you have questi
 ons about what board to get\, please E-Mailfpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSi
 nce the space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the rec
 ommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  A
 ttendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
