CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We had planned on adding division and add w/ carry\, but there 
 has been a change.  Since the divider opcode took quite a while\, we will b
 e covering how to get the divider working from the ground up.  This will be
  done using the ISE simulator and simple test bench code.  We will cover th
 e divider (version 3 and version 4) and also simulate the CPU itself.\n\nWe
  should not need the actual boards for this part.  Even so\, I suggest brin
 ging them in case we have time at the end of class.\n\nRequired Items:\n1. 
 Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensure you already have the ISE i
 nstalled!!  We will not have time to wait for the install process to comple
 te (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xilinx.com/suppo
 rt/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and 
 download the ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spartan 6 or gre
 ater FPGA development board (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer the Mojo or Digi
 lent Nexys3.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev board.\n\nWe are to a point in
  the class where anyone wishing to join will need to E-Mail fpga@unallocate
 dspace.org.  The reason being that we will need to verify that you know VHD
 L well\, and have a development board already.\n\nBecause of the cost of FP
 GA dev boards\, we will not have extras.  If you have questions about what 
 board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nWe have recently
  been given 'academic' status from Digilent Inc (http://www.digilentinc.com
 ).  This means that the instructor can purchase boards from Digilent at the
  academic price.  This discount will only apply to people who are attending
  the class regularly!\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would l
 ike to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by
  no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100
 % free to all!
