DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130726T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130726T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:874f4ggn9ejgf8sacdpggf55ak@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130726T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be covering using Python (pyserial) to communicate with
  an Arduino.  This will include sending data back and forth as well as turn
 ing pins on and off via serial.  \n\nPlease ensure your laptop has BOTH Pyt
 hon and pyserial installed.  Verify that pyserial is installed by typing 'i
 mport pyserial' in the Python interactive prompt.  If you have issues with 
 this\, or do not know how to invoke the interactive prompt just shoot an E-
 Mail to arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nRequired Items\n1. Arduino & USB c
 able\n2. Breadboard & jumpers\n3. Laptop with Arduino software installed AN
 D Python with pyserial\n\nProvides Items\n1. LEDs\n2. Resistors\n\nIf you n
 eed any items in the required items section\, please E-Mail arduino@unalloc
 atedspace.org.  We have a few of all of the required items\, but we need to
  know how many to prepare.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we wo
 uld like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It 
 is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, i
 s 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130816T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130816T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:874f4ggn9ejgf8sacdpggf55ak@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130816T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:This Arduino Night will cover using 4 wire touch screens.  Thes
 e are touch screens from some old Garmin GPS units that were cannibalized. 
 \n\nEveryone will need to have Python installed on their laptop in order to
  see a plot of the points from the touch pad.  Additionally\, you will need
  to have a file called graphics.py (link) installed in site-packages (C:\\P
 ythonXY\\Lib\\site-packages for Windows\, /usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/site-pac
 kages for Linux).  You can simply copy the file from wherever you downloade
 d it to into the appropriate directory for your OS.  If you have issues and
  would like help\, please E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nRequired 
 Items\n1. Arduino & USB cable\n2. Laptop with Arduino software installed\n3
 . Python and graphics.py installed if you want to see dot plots\n\nProvided
  Items\n1. 4 wire resistive touch screen (hand soldered by Jake)\n\nIf you 
 need any items in the required items section\, please E-Mail arduino@unallo
 catedspace.org.  We have a few of all of the required items\, but we need t
 o know how many to prepare.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we w
 ould like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It
  is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, 
 is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130823T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130823T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:874f4ggn9ejgf8sacdpggf55ak@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130823T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Please bring your Arduino(s) and your project / project ideas w
 ith you this Friday.\n \nLets share what we are working on. And what issues
  and difficulties we are having.\n \nWe can also treat this as a refresher 
 class to pick up any topics from previous classes that anyone has missed or
  is not confident in.
