DTEND:20140809T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:8aufip2n66uohaf0mm01k29eq8@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Mike Huhn\, K3TEZ will discuss the Pixie 2\, a minimalist QRPp 
 CW \ntransceiver\, with regard to its roots\, evolution\, and design. Follo
 wing \nthe initial talk\, there will be a brief receiving demonstration tha
 t \nwill compare the Pixie 2 and another direct conversion transceiver with
  \nan FT-817 superhet transceiver and a Q&A session. \n\nNOTE:  (For those 
 of you non Ham Types) QRPp means that you can work the \nworld with less po
 wer than you have in your Bathroom night light!  CW \nstands for Continuous
  Wave which is another term for using Morse Code.   \nIf you have an intere
 st in Electronics at all\, you need to be here!   \nMike will describe how 
 this radio works and even give us a demo on how 2 \ndifferent radios can so
 und different just because of the different type \nof circuit! \n\nWe'll al
 so be talking about some of the upcoming events such as the MD \nQSO Party 
 which starts right after Ham Night. \n\nSo Come one.. Come ALL to our next 
 Ham Night at UAS! 
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ham Radio Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
