BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20110928T210000Z
DTEND:20110929T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:-WWW-UNALLOCATEDSPACE-ORG-CALENDAR-__PUBLIC__-0000000078
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Calling all InfoSec professionals\, those looking to break into
  the field and everyone else who’d like some free pizza and beer! \n  \nThi
 s Wednesday\, September 28 @ 5 PM\, Unallocated Space is proud to present T
 enable Network Security‘s Jack Daniel. \n  \nJack’s first 20 minute session
 \, “From sock puppets to CSOs\, how to get your message heard” is about usi
 ng storytelling techniques and ideas to improve how effectively we communic
 ate with others–an area where many of us in InfoSec could use a little help
 . \n  \nThe second topic is “Stress and Burnout in Infosec Careers”. This w
 ill be a review of some research Jack is working on along with a few friend
 ly experts in the community. He’s got some lessons and observations to shar
 e\, after which he hopes to have an open discussion with you! \n  \nNo matt
 er what stage of the InfoSec career path you’re on\, whether you’re looking
  for a job or happy where you’re at\, you’ll want to stop by UAS for some p
 ointers and friendly networking. It’s also a great time to check out UAS if
  you’ve never been here before.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tenable InfoSec Career Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
