UID:-WWW-UNALLOCATEDSPACE-ORG-CALENDAR-__PUBLIC__-0000000096
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Most of the community is in agreement that real pentesting is n
 ot in the tools\, or even in the process\, but it's in the mindset and the 
 creativity.  But unless you've got some exceptional natural skills\, it tak
 es time and practice to change the way you approach problem solving. \n \nS
 trogonaut is looking to put together a curriculum and wants to discuss.  Su
 bjects are: \n- Problem solving\, conventional wisdom/coding practices\, an
 d where \nthey fail. \n- Unorthodox approaches to problems\, large-scale sy
 stem analysis and \ninteraction. \n \n- The Penetration Testing Execution S
 tandard \n  - Where it shines \n  - Where is needs help \n \n-  Penetration
  Testing with Backtrack \n   - Applying the tools to the theory and the for
 m \n \n-  Social Engineering \n  - Norms of human behavior \n  - Cultural s
 ignificance and unique customs \n  - Built-in trust relationships and their
  exploitation \n  - Manners\, politeness\, and expectations \n  - NLP\, pre
 texting\, suggestion\, and manipulation \n  - Semi-automated exploitation w
 ith SET. \n \nAdvanced add-ons would involve fuzzing\, reverse engineering\
 , exploit design\, etc. \n \n \nUpdate: Pre-discussion libations start @ 5\
 , kickoff at 6...
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: PTES\, PWB\, SET\, and the mindset of hacking
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20120107T220000Z
DTEND:20120108T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:-WWW-UNALLOCATEDSPACE-ORG-CALENDAR-__PUBLIC__-0000000097
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Georgia Weidman from Neohapsis\, Inc will be teaching a 4 hour 
 session on using Metaploit for penetration testing. \n \nThis class will be
 gin with the basics of using the Metasploit Framework. We will continue on 
 following a penetration test methodology for using Metasploit to exploit vu
 lnerable systems in a lab environment. This class is suitable for those wit
 h no background in Metasploit or penetration testing as well as experienced
  or novice penetration testers who want to add the Metasploit Framework to 
 their arsenal. \n \nAttendees will need a computer capable of running virtu
 al machines. Having vmware or virtual box already installed would be helpfu
 l but no one ever reads directions anyways! In addition to virtual machines
 \, the student handout will have installers for vmware trials or free versi
 ons depending on platforms. \n \nJoin us for some Metasploit and pentesting
  goodness! \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Metasploit for Pentesting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
