DESCRIPTION:Buy\, sell and gawk at all the precious junk that other hobbyis
 ts crave. \n \n Entrance Donation:     Adults $5\, Kids under 16 FREE  \n \
 n Here are just some of the hobbies represented last year: \n \nR/C (boats\
 , planes\, tanks\, cars\, trains\, geese\, monsters) \nRobotics (competitio
 n\, combat\, R2D2\, micro-bots\, junk-bots) \nElectronics (hackers\, makers
 \, crackers\, phreaks\, HAMS) \nMechanical (steam engines\, CNC\, animatron
 ics\, whimsical) \n \nAnd some of the precious stuff (a.k.a. junk) you'll f
 ind: \n \nmotors\, gears\, tools\, parts\, radios\, televisions\, monitors 
 \nbatteries\, materials\, wheels\, circuits\, gadgets\, cases\, plans \ncom
 plete projects\, never-completed projects\, computers \nelectronic musical 
 instruments\, lights\, models\, books \nwearable electronics\, and much\, m
 uch more \n \nhttp://sites.google.com/site/technoswapfest2/ \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:National Electronics Museum @ 1745 West Nursery Road\, Linthicum M
 D
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Techno Swapfest 2012
TRANSP:OPAQUE
