CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:On Saturday\, February 25th\, National Electronics Museum (NEM)
  will be holding it's 8th Annual Techno-Swap-Fest. This is a perfect opport
 unity to meet people with similar interest\, find what your looking for\, t
 rade up\, trade down\, or donate what you don't need. All entrance proceeds
  support the National Electronics. Adults $5\, Kids under 16 FREE.\n\nThe U
 AS is a club sponsor and will be attending this event. Don't forget to visi
 t us! We will be more then happy to tell you about the exciting things we d
 o. We will be bartering\, selling and accepting donates at this event\, as 
 well be entering in a contest for the most unusual\, least useful\, best du
 st collector item\, so come out and see what it is. Vote for us!\n\nLearn m
 ore at https://www.meetup.com/Unallocated-Space/events/236366485/ .\n\n====
 \n\nAttention All Hobbyists\n\n* Is your shop so cluttered you can barely w
 ork on your projects? \n* Did you buy something online that didn't fit into
  your plans? \n* Are you still looking for that perfect gadget\, part or to
 ol?\n\nIf you answered YES or NO to any of these questions\, you need to at
 tend the 8th Annual Techno-Swap-Fest to buy\, sell and gawk at all the prec
 ious junk that other hobbyists crave.\n\nHere are just some of the hobbies 
 represented last year at the Techno-Swap-Fest:\n\n* R/C (boats\, planes\, t
 anks\, cars\, trains\, geese\, monsters) \n* Robotics (competition\, combat
 \, R2D2\, micro-bots\, junk-bots) \n* Electronics (hackers\, makers\, crack
 ers\, phreaks\, HAMS) \n* Mechanical (steam engines\, CNC\, animatronics\, 
 whimsical)\n\nAnd some of the precious stuff (a.k.a. junk) you'll find:\n\n
 * motors\, gears\, tools\, parts\, radios\, televisions\, monitors \n* batt
 eries\, materials\, wheels\, circuits\, gadgets\, cases\, plans \n* complet
 e projects\, never-completed projects\, computers \n* electronic musical in
 struments\, lights\, models\, books \n* wearable electronics\, and much\, m
 uch more\n\nMore Reading...\n\nhttps://sites.google.com/site/technoswapfest
 2/ \nhttps://sites.google.com/site/technoswapfest2/sponsors
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:National Electronics Museum\, 1745 W Nursery Rd\, Linthicum Height
 s\, MD 21090\, United States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:TENTATIVE
SUMMARY:Techno-Swap-Fest - Join Unallocated Space!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
