DESCRIPTION:Matthew is presenting the first session of a basic Linux class\
 , based on a commercial "Linux System Administrator I" class\, with permiss
 ion from the vendor of the class.  \n\nThe topics of the course start off w
 ith the basics\, but the class will continue beyond the propsed eight-weeks
  if students want to move on to advanced topics:\n\n1. Accessing the comman
 d line.\n2. Managing files from the command line.\n3. Getting help in Linux
 \n4. Creating\, viewing\, and editing text files.\n5. Managing local Linux 
 users and groups.\n6. Controlling access to files with Linux file system pe
 rmissions.\n7. Monitoring and managing Linux processes.\n8. Controlling Ser
 vices and Daemons.\n9. Configuring and Securing OpenSSH Service.\n10. Analy
 zing and storing logs.\n11. Managing Linux networking.\n12. Archiving and c
 opying files between systems.\n13. Installing and updating software package
 s.\n14. Accessing Linux file systems.\n15. Using virtualized systems.\n\nSi
 nce Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that
  the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a require
 ment! Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, United 
 States
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Basic Linux System Administration
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
