UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130514T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Mostly carrying over from last week.\n\nAgenda\n\n1. Install/Ru
 n Xiliinx ISE (http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xi
 linx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html - ISE Design Suite)\n2. Compile and u
 pload blinky lights bit file\n3. Modify blinky lights code to change rate o
 f blink\n4. Use DCM instead of divider to vary blink rate\n\nRequired Items
 \n\n1. Xilinx based Spartan 3 or higher FPGA\n2. Laptop running Windows or 
 Linux (OSX will not work!)\n3. Breadboard and LEDs if your FPGA board does 
 not have LEDs\n4. Laptop must have ~ 30GB of free disk space for Xilinx ISE
 \n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we will not have extras.  If y
 ou have questions about what board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocateds
 pace.org.\n\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would like to men
 tion that the recommended donation for this class is $10. It is by no means
  a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to
  all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130521T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130521T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130521T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be covering analog to digital conversion using an FPGA.
   The current plan is to use pre-programmed Arduino's to act as the analog 
 to digital converter (ADC) instead of a dedicated ADC chip.  The FPGA will 
 be processing the data from the ADC and outputting data based on the ADC in
 put.\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensur
 e you already have the ISE installed!!  We will not have time to wait for t
 he install process to complete (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out
  http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downlo
 adNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. 
 Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA development board (must be Xilinx!!).
   We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev 
 board.\n4. Arduino if you have one\n5. Jumper wires\n\nProvided Items:\n1. 
 Arduino if you do not have one.\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\,
  we will not have extras.  If you have questions about what board to get\, 
 please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSince the space runs off of don
 ations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this cl
 ass is $10. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and
  this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130528T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130528T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130528T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be covering building custom blocks and then using them 
 in VHDL modules.  If time permits\, we will also cover using outside input 
 in the form of push buttons.\n\nAgenda:\n1. Design a module that slows down
  an input clock\n2. Design a module that uses the above module to blink an 
 LED at a slower rate\n3. Design a module that takes two inputs and either i
 ncrements or decrements a counter that is displayed on using the FPGA dev b
 oard's LEDs.\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Plea
 se ensure you already have the ISE installed!!  We will not have time to wa
 it for the install process to complete (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  C
 heck out http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/e
 n/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Suite for your 
 OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA development board (must be Xi
 linx!!).  We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB cable for your F
 PGA dev board.\n4. Breadboard\n5. Jumper wires\n\nProvided Items:\n1. Push 
 button switches (tactile)\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we wi
 ll not have extras.  If you have questions about what board to get\, please
  E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations
 \, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is
  $10. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this 
 class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130604T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130604T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130604T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be covering interfacing with 7 segment displays.  This 
 is the precursor to the next class which will cover interfacing with 2x20 c
 haracter LCD screens.\n\nAgenda:\n1. Determine pinout of 7 segment display\
 n2. Create a map of the pins\n3. Flash all segments at once\n4. Create a RO
 M lookup table to count 0-F\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE i
 nstalled.  Please ensure you already have the ISE installed!!  We will not 
 have time to wait for the install process to complete (it usually takes 15-
 30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/c
 ontent/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design 
 Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA development bo
 ard (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB c
 able for your FPGA dev board.\n4. Breadboard\n5. Jumper wires\n\nProvided I
 tems:\n1. 7 segment display\n2. Resistors (current limiting)\n\nBecause of 
 the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we will not have extras.  If you have questio
 ns about what board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSi
 nce the space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the rec
 ommended donation for this class is $10. It is by no means a requirement!  
 Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130611T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130611T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130611T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be starting the LCD interface project.  The goal for th
 e night will be to get the finite state machine running properly.\n\nRequir
 ed Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensure you already 
 have the ISE installed!!  We will not have time to wait for the install pro
 cess to complete (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xi
 linx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-t
 ools.html and download the ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Sp
 artan 3 or greater FPGA development board (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer th
 e Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev board.\n4. Bre
 adboard\n5. Jumper wires\n\nProvided Items:\n1. LCD display\n2. LEDs for de
 bugging\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we will not have extras
 .  If you have questions about what board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unall
 ocatedspace.org.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would like t
 o mention that the recommended donation for this class is $10. It is by no 
 means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% fr
 ee to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
