UID:gjdnkdq4bookhdkfmsh727abt8@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130625T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be using push buttons to interface with the FPGA as wel
 l as learning how to debounce the inputs.  If time permits\, we will also c
 over First In First Out (FIFO) buffers.\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with 
 Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensure you already have the ISE installed!!  
 We will not have time to wait for the install process to complete (it usual
 ly takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/
 index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the
  ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA de
 velopment board (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys I
 I.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev board.\n4. Breadboard\n5. Jumper wires\n
 \nProvided Items:\n1. LEDs\n2. Resistors\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev
  boards\, we will not have extras.  If you have questions about what board 
 to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSince the space runs o
 ff of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation fo
 r this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the spa
 ce\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
