DESCRIPTION:Bring all your required materials!\n  Notebook\n  Pen/Pencil\n 
  Scientific Calculator\n  Variable DC power supply: http://www.circuitspeci
 alists.com/csi1501.html\n  Corey owns the power supply in the link\; it see
 ms worth the $30.\n  We have 3 power supplies available on a first come\, f
 irst serve basis.  I don't recommend relying on there being one available.\
 n  Resistor assortment http://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/RS125/RS125
 -ND-7108\n    Radio Shack and other retailers carry similar assortments\n  
 Digital Multimeter: http://www.circuitspecialists.com/digital-multimeter-cs
 i2010.html\n    Any Digital Multimeter will work\, as long as it has AC/DC 
 volts\, AC/DC amps\, and can measure up to at least 2M ohms\n    You get wh
 at you pay for with meters.  You don't need a $100 fluke\, but I don't reco
 mmend a $5 Harbor Freight special.\n    Your meter will stick with you for 
 a very long time if you get a good one\n  Breadboard http://www.circuitspec
 ialists.com/wb-102+j.html\n    Radio Shack\, Sparkfun\, Microcenter and all
  sorts of other places sell breadboards!\n  Jumper Wires (with Alligator cl
 ips)\n    http://www.radioshack.com/product/index.jsp?productID=2062660\n  
   http://www.circuitspecialists.com/m000f0002.html\nThese are the most hand
 y things to have in your tool box for electronics\, seriously.\n\nThis week
  we will be getting familiar with our equipment\, measuring resistors\, vol
 tage\, and current\, applying Ohm's law to series circuits.  We will also b
 e looking at some basic troubleshooting techniques.\n\nSince Unallocated Sp
 ace runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended d
 onation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement! Attendance t
 o the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Electronics Fundamentals Class Series
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
