UID:goss50shgjpsth6vibn87fg17s@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:GOTA with HSMM-Mesh!\n\nGot an old LInksys Router?  Wanna reuse
  it in a way that can help others?\n\nBring it to the Space!  June 14th fro
 m 10am to 3pm.\n\nThis event will be a hands on GOTA (Get On The Air) event
 !  HSMM-Mesh is a topology and culture of using this older technology to be
 nefit others by creating a wireless Mesh Network.  The Goal is to get Easte
 rn Central Maryland into the Mesh and Bridge between Baltimore and DC and e
 ventually all the way to NYC!\n\nEven if you don't have equipment but want 
 to learn more about this unique use of Technology\, come out and hang with 
 us!  There may be extra equipment you can practice with.\n\nTo see if your 
 equipment will work with this\, check out \nhttp://www.broadband-hamnet.org
 /section-blog/37-hardware-faqs/101-supported-hardware.html for more informa
 tion.\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ham Radio - Meshnet Tutorial and GOTA
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20140201T180000Z
DTEND:20140201T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gqgffsfvaofuq42j9tbaia5pu8@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:William Thompson (N3DC) is cleaning out his ham shack and has g
 raciously offered to give away his gear to fellow (and up-and-coming) hams.
   Around 1300 this Saturday (February 1st)\, we'll be raffling them off.  A
 mong various smaller items\, he plans to give away a number of radios:\n\n 
  Kenwood THD7A - 2m/70cm handheld transceiver\n  Kenwood 2600 - 2m 2.5W han
 dheld transceiver\n  Icom IC-R7000 - 25-2000MHz desktop receiver\n  Icom IC
 -R7100 - 25-1025MHz desktop receiver\n  Icom IC-706 MKII - HF/2m/70cm mobil
 e transceiver\n  MFJ 9015 - 15m CW transceiver\n  MFJ 906 - 6m manual tuner
  with built-in SWR meter\n  JRC NRD-535 - HF desktop receiver with speaker\
 n  AEA PK 900 - Data (Packet/RTTY/CW/...) controller\n  Yaesu FT-50 - 2m/70
 cm handheld transceiver/scanner\n  PC Electronics TC-1 70cm 10W Amateur TV 
 transmitter\n\nWe'll raffle everything off using numbered tickets.  There i
 s no charge for a ticket.  Just show up.  But you can earn extra tickets:\n
   - Dues-paying UAS member?  Get an extra ticket.\n  - Got your license in 
 the last year?  Get an extra ticket.\n  - Upgraded your license in the last
  year?  Get an extra ticket.\n  - Ready to answer some FCC exam questions? 
  Get an extra ticket.\n\nHope to see you there!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ham Raffle
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
