CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be working with SPI based SRAM.  The SRAM chip will be 
 the 23LC512 (datasheet link: http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDo
 c/20005155B.pdf).\n\nAgenda:\n     1. What is SRAM\n     2. Review datashee
 t\n     3. Use SPI library to write to and read from the SRAM\n     4. Writ
 e to and read from the SRAM by hand\n\n     \nIf you cannot attend the clas
 s in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to th
 e Google Hangout.  The hangout will generally be started just before class 
 (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, please E-Mail ardui
 no@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classe
 s can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwU
 VhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three day
 s before a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind
  (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board 
 does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP
 \, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. 
 Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are
  okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5.
  Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. 
 Jumper wires for your breadboard\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. SRAM chip (2
 3LC512 http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/20005155B.pdf)\n    
  \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to menti
 on that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a 
 requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the sp
 ace\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
