UID:gsrj3pt4504vre2b6q3h3jn17o@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150417T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Per a request at the last class\, we will be writing to and rea
 ding from SD cards.  \n\nPlease bring an SD card if you can.  There will on
 ly be two available for use!!!  Also\, the cards must be SD\, not the small
 er cards.  All cards should be 8GB or less and be formatted to FAT16 or FAT
 32.  Larger sizes might work\, but I haven't tested it.\n\nAgenda:\n     1.
  Look over the LC Studio breakout boards\n     2. Interfacing with SD cards
 \n     3. Resistor dividers\n     4. Wiring up the breakout board\n     5. 
 Run demo code\n     6. Create custom code to write ADC samples and then rea
 d them back\n\n     \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E-Mail ard
 uino@unallocatedspace.org\n and ask to be added to the Google Hangout.  The
  hangout will generally \nbe started just before class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If 
 you do not have an \ninvite by 7:15\, please E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspac
 e.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can be found at 
 https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sha
 ring.  The slides are generally made during the three days before a class.\
 n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega
 \, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board does not have USB 
 programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bu
 s Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the lo
 ng one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are okay for now)\n  
    4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop with the A
 rduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for y
 our breadboard\n     7. Variable resistor\n     8. SD card if you have one.
   Preferably <= 4GB\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. LC Studio SD card breakou
 t board\n     \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would 
 like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is b
 y no means a requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attenda
 nce to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
