DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20150501T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20150501T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:gsrj3pt4504vre2b6q3h3jn17o@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150501T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:I am super late getting to the slides for this class.  The basi
 c plan is to play with transistors to control LEDs and DC motors.  If we ge
 t through everything\, then the next class will hopefully cover H bridges f
 or reversing DC motors.  The agenda is short since the class could go way o
 ver the allotted time.\n\nFeel free to bring your own DC motor.  We have a 
 small collection of motors at the space.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. What is a tran
 sitor?\n     2. Why use one?\n     3. Look over datasheet\n     4. Hands on
  with LEDs\n     5. Hands on with DC motors \n\n     \nIf you cannot attend
  the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be ad
 ded to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will generally be started just befo
 re class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, please E-M
 ail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previo
 us classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0
 G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the 
 three days before a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of 
 some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If yo
 ur board does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a programme
 r (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\
 n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small square-ish
  ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer
 \n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\
 n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Tra
 nsistor (part number TBD)\n     2. DC motor\n     \n\nSince Unallocated Spa
 ce runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended do
 nation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it does 
 help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 
 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, Unit
 ed States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20140926T230000Z
DTEND:20140927T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:h07e9kaigtn21l9n7kiscm86a4@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Back by popular demand :D\n\nWe will go over what the Arduino i
 s\, how to use the IDE\, what LEDs are\, and create a blinky light sketch. 
  If time permits\, we will move into talking about Wiring functions\, C dat
 a types\, and custom C functions.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Instructor introducti
 on\n     2. Overall plan for the series of classes\n     3. What is an Ardu
 ino?\n     4. Loading and using the Arduino IDE\n     5. What is an LED?\n 
     6. What are resistors for and why does my LED care?\n     7. Create a b
 linky light example\n     8. (Time permitting) Other Wiring functions\n    
  9. (Time permitting) C data types\n     10. (Time permitting) Custom C fun
 ctions\n\n     \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@
 unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hangou
 t will be started just before class (6:45-7:00 PM).\n\n\nThe slides for the
  upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/fol
 derview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are genera
 lly made during the three days before a class.\n\n\nRequired Items:\n     1
 . An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove
 \, etc)\n     2. If your board does not have USB programming built in\, you
  will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, a
 nother Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, thoug
 h the small square-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your b
 oard and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linu
 x\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard\n\nProvided
  Items:\n     1. Breadboard and jumpers (if you don't have any of either)\n
      2. LEDs\n     3. Resistors\n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of dona
 tions\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this cla
 ss is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it does help us keep the li
 ghts on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
