DESCRIPTION:Interrupts\, looping\, and program flow\n\nMaking things happen
  when it needs to and when (and how many times) you want it to.\n\nBring yo
 ur laptops and Arduinos. If you have LEDs and pushbuttons please bring them
 . Firebuttons with safety switches would be awesome.\n\nThose of you who ma
 y have a safety firebutton in your collection\, this would be the night to 
 bring them. You will be writing code\, but the end result will be worth it.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20121201T000000Z
DTEND:20121201T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:hn3pg36405uo598mtnihhuvipk@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Agenda\n1. Transistors (should have done this at the last class
 ). Using them to turn on LEDs and DC motors.\n2. Two way communication to t
 he Arduino using Serial.read() and Serial.println().\n3. Using tactile swit
 ches (tiny buttons) to toggle two LEDs.\n\nRequirements\n\n1. Arduino of so
 me variety.\n2. Laptop with USB ports.\n3. Breadboard of some type. Full si
 ze is best\, but small ones will work as well.\n\nProvided\n\n1. 2N2222 Tra
 nsistors (Datasheet)\n2. DC motors\n3. LEDs\n4. Tactile switches\n\nIf ther
 e are any questions\, comments\, suggestions\, etc then please contact Prot
 o17 at dmp250net@gmail.com.\n\nWe have spares of all the required items.  I
 f you will need to use any of the spares\, please let Proto17 know.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
