DESCRIPTION:What would be a better way to prepare for the following week's 
 Unallocated Space (UAS) Community Tech Swap Meet/Garage Sale (6/8)\, than w
 ith a Unallocated BBQ and Sprint Cleaning (5/25)?\n\nCome on out and enjoy 
 an Unallocated BBQ! Whether your a meat and potatoes kind of guy/gal or jus
 t enjoy snacking on delicious home made foods\, there will be something for
  everyone.\n\nThe Unallocated Space welcomes you and your friends to come o
 ut and enjoy a bite to eat between 11:30PM and 2PM. We will also begin clea
 ning/improving the space from 11:30pm to whenever.  Everyone is always welc
 ome to just come and stop by\, but your participation is always appreciated
 .\n\n◦﻿﻿﻿﻿Add ﻿what you're bringing to the spreadsheet (Google Doc)\nhttps:
 //docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvqXQ2p0sEvCdGlUdkRSeXNnYVlsRGNmT3BX
 eDF0d3c&usp=sharing\n\nIf you have any questions or comments\, please e-mai
 l info@unallocatedspace.org. Since the space runs off of donations\, we wou
 ld like to mention that all donation are greatly appreciated. It is by no m
 eans a requirement! Attendance to the space\, and this event\, is 100% free
  to all!\n\nNote: This type of event typically gets between 10-30 participa
 nts\, but many of participants don't check-in using social media.\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Unallocated Space 512 Shaw Ct #105 Severn\, Ma
 ryland 21144
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Unallocated BBQ and Spring Cleaning
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
