DESCRIPTION:It's taken us a while to get around to organizing it\, but it's
  finally here.\n\nI'm REALLY excited to announce the first official Unalloc
 ated Space Hackthon on November 8th and 9th. \n\nLearn more here: https://u
 nallocated.github.io/hackathon\n\nOh yeah. This is legit. We're gonna lock 
 in for 24 hours\, poison our bodies with caffeine and junk food\, jam out s
 ome code and rebuild our core services infrastructure. \n\nEveryone can hel
 p out. It's all outlined on the link above and we've got many different rol
 es that need to be filled. While code is our primary focus\, we'll need muc
 h much more.\n\n We've also got no shortage of projects. We are open to con
 sidering new projects\, but it must be considered a part of the core servic
 es infrastructure. Anyone who would like to lead a project can reach out to
  me using the contact form on the website here: https://unallocated.github.
 io/hackathon/contact/. You can learn more about becoming a project lead her
 e: https://unallocated.github.io/hackathon/projectlead\n\nThis event will b
 e preceded by a Git Workshop so that we can get everyone on the same page. 
 More information on that will be here: https://unallocated.github.io/hackat
 hon/gitworkshop/
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, United 
 States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UAS Hackathon0
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
