DESCRIPTION:Cancelled - there are no RSVPs and I have a family appointment 
 that I must attend. Please RSVP for Saturday and/or next Tuesday's class if
  you are interested. \n\nhttp://meetu.ps/tyr1j\n\n\nAll \,\n\nHow exciting 
 does build a computer from scratch sound? \n\nWhether learning how to build
  your very own computer or just building one in the company of others\, you
  will enjoy this (3 day / 8 hr) class. And let’s not forget\, Valentine's D
 ay is right around the corner\, so join us at Unallocated Space (UAS) and l
 earn how to build a computer from scratch. \n\nSince the space runs off of 
 donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this
  class is $10 a day. It is by no means a requirement! Attendance to the spa
 ce\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!\n\nv\\r\n\nBuddy\nTeach\, Learn\
 , Build (Party)\nhttp://www.unallocatedspace.org\n\n====\n\nEvent Details:\
 n\nTuesday\, February 5\, 2013 (7PM to 9PM)\n\nClass 1 / 2 hrs (Part 1) Har
 dware Basics - Building a computer from scratch gives you the perfect machi
 ne for your needs\, but it can be daunting the first time around. For our f
 irst lesson in building your own PC\, we start with a little computer hardw
 are basics. -- (Part 2) Choose and Buy Your Parts - In this lesson\, we'll 
 show you how to most effectively pick out and shop for your parts. \n\nSatu
 rday or Sunday (TBD by the Class)\n\nCass 2 / 3 hrs (Optional) – Fieldtrip 
 to Micro Center – Let’s be honest\, these classes are not complete until we
  do a fieldtrip to our local computer supply store. As determined by the cl
 ass\, we will choose a day to carpool to Micro Center (or another store of 
 our choosing).\n\nTuesday\, February 12\, 2013 (7PM to 10PM)\n\nClass 3 / 3
  hrs (Part 1) Building the Computer - Assembling your computer can seem dau
 nting\, but it's actually pretty easy. In part 1\, we show you step-by-step
  how to put everything together. -- (Part 2) Installing Your Operating Syst
 em (e.g. Ubuntu http://www.ubuntu.com \,Windows\, etc.) - Once you've put i
 t together\, you're past the difficult portion. With installing your operat
 ing system and get everything up and running. -- (Part 3) Show Off & Furthe
 r Resources - This night we will show off our creations and share any resou
 rces we discovered.\n\nLocation: Unallocated Space\nAddress:‎ 512 Shaw Cour
 t # 105\, Severn\, MD 21144\nhttp://www.unallocatedspace.org/uas/about-us/\
 n\nAdapted from: \nhttp://lifehacker.com/5828747/how-to-build-a-computer-fr
 om-scratch-the-complete-guide
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space (Severn\, MD)
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cancelled - How to Build a Computer from Scratch - Class 1
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
