CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be creating a new VHDL module that counts up and down u
 sing two buttons.  This will also involve switch debouncing.\n\nThe slides 
 for the upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.
 com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbGNiRVRBUFN4cWs&usp=sharing.  The slides are
  generally made during the three days before a class.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. O
 verview of last class\n     2. Counting with LEDs\n     3. Modify design to
  use a button\n     4. Debouncing\n     5. Modify design to debounce\n     
 6. Modify design to count up and down\n\nIf you would like to join the clas
 s\, then please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.  We also stream the class
  on Google Hangouts.  Please send an E-Mail to fpga@unallocatedspace.org if
  you would like to join the Google Hangout.\n\n**IMPORTANT** You *MUST* hav
 e ISE (not Vivado!) installed prior to the start of class!!!  ISE can take 
 upwards of 30 minutes to an hour to install.  We will not have time to wait
  for ISE to be installed.  Please go to http://www.xilinx.com/support/downl
 oad/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download
  the ISE Design Suite package for your operating system.  If you have licen
 sing or installation issues\, please contact fpga@unallocatedspace.org\n\nR
 equired Items:\n     1. FPGA development board with Spartan 3 or Spartan 6\
 n     2. USB cable for programming\n     3. JTAG programmer if your board d
 oes not have USB\n     4. Laptop **with ISE installed** and either wired or
  wireless network connectivity\n     5. Breadboard and jumpers (please E-Ma
 il fpga@unallocatedspace.org if you don't have one or both of these so the 
 instructor can make sure to bring enough extras)\n\nProvided Items:\n     1
 . Push buttons (only needed if your development board does not have multipl
 e buttons)\n     2. Resistors (2K Ohm\, only needed if you use external pus
 h buttons)\n\nWe have been given 'academic' status from Digilent Inc (http:
 //www.digilentinc.com).  This means that the instructor can (sometimes) pur
 chase boards from Digilent at the academic price.  This discount will only 
 apply to people who are attending the class regularly and is on a case-by-c
 ase basis from Digilent.\n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\,
  we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $
 5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this cla
 ss\, is 100% free to all!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20140603T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20140603T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:jbt1t2ktr3cudc2dutr4ff30j0@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20140603T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be starting the first of two classes aimed at interfaci
 ng our FPGAs to SRAM (datasheet). This class will focus on wiring\, state m
 achines\, tri-state logic\, and processes.  We might not get through all of
  the topics.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can be fou
 nd at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbGNiRVRBUFN4cWs&u
 sp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three days before a c
 lass.  An E-Mail will be sent to those attending the class via Google Hango
 uts with instructions for getting an SRAM chip.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Wire up
  SRAM chip to the FPGA\n     2. Modify and upload provided test design for 
 specific FPGA dev board\n     3. Intro to state machines\n     4. Implement
 ing state machines in VHDL\n     5. Create pseudo-code state machines for w
 riting and reading the SRAM\n     6. Intro to tri-state buffers (inout pins
  in VHDL)\n     7. Creating slower clock using a dedicated process\n     \n
 \nIf you would like to join the class\, then please E-Mail fpga@unallocated
 space.org.  We also stream the class on Google Hangouts.  Please send an E-
 Mail to fpga@unallocatedspace.org if you would like to join the Google Hang
 out.\n\n**IMPORTANT** You *MUST* have ISE (not Vivado!) installed prior to 
 the start of class!!!  ISE can take upwards of 30 minutes to an hour to ins
 tall.  We will not have time to wait for ISE to be installed.  Please go to
  http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downlo
 adNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Suite package for your 
 operating system.  If you have licensing or installation issues\, please co
 ntact fpga@unallocatedspace.org\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. FPGA developmen
 t board with Spartan 3 or Spartan 6\n     2. USB cable for programming\n   
   3. JTAG programmer if your board does not have USB\n     4. Laptop **with
  ISE installed** and either wired or wireless network connectivity\n     5.
  Breadboard and jumpers (please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org if you don
 't have one or both of these so the instructor can make sure to bring enoug
 h extras)\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Alliance AS6C62256 256KB parallel SRA
 M\n     2. Test code for the SRAM\n\nWe have been given 'academic' status f
 rom Digilent Inc (http://www.digilentinc.com).  This means that the instruc
 tor can (sometimes) purchase boards from Digilent at the academic price.  T
 his discount will only apply to people who are attending the class regularl
 y and is on a case-by-case basis from Digilent.\n\nSince Unallocated Space 
 runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donat
 ion for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to t
 he space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20140610T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20140610T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:jbt1t2ktr3cudc2dutr4ff30j0@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20140610T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:This will be the second (and probably last) class on creating a
  state machine to drive SRAM.  We will start off with finishing the write s
 tate machine\, then add in the code for reading.  After that we will create
  a test bench to test reading and writing.  Finally we will wire up the SRA
 M and run our design to write to and then read from the SRAM\n\nThe slides 
 for the upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.
 com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbGNiRVRBUFN4cWs&usp=sharing.  The slides are
  generally made during the three days before a class.  An E-Mail will be se
 nt to those attending the class via Google Hangouts with instructions for g
 etting an SRAM chip.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Finish the write state machine\n  
    2. Add in the read state machine\n     3. Verify our design with a test 
 bench\n     4. Wire up the SRAM to the FPGA\n     5. Run our writing and re
 ading design\n     \n\nIf you would like to join the class\, then please E-
 Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.  We also stream the class on Google Hangout
 s.  Please send an E-Mail to fpga@unallocatedspace.org if you would like to
  join the Google Hangout.\n\n**IMPORTANT** You *MUST* have ISE (not Vivado!
 ) installed prior to the start of class!!!  ISE can take upwards of 30 minu
 tes to an hour to install.  We will not have time to wait for ISE to be ins
 talled.  Please go to http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/con
 tent/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Su
 ite package for your operating system.  If you have licensing or installati
 on issues\, please contact fpga@unallocatedspace.org\n\nRequired Items:\n  
    1. FPGA development board with Spartan 3 or Spartan 6\n     2. USB cable
  for programming\n     3. JTAG programmer if your board does not have USB\n
      4. Laptop **with ISE installed** and either wired or wireless network 
 connectivity\n     5. Breadboard and jumpers (please E-Mail fpga@unallocate
 dspace.org if you don't have one or both of these so the instructor can mak
 e sure to bring enough extras)\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Alliance AS6C622
 56 256KB parallel SRAM\n     2. Test code for the SRAM (The bug from last c
 lass has been fixed!)\n\nWe have been given 'academic' status from Digilent
  Inc (http://www.digilentinc.com).  This means that the instructor can (som
 etimes) purchase boards from Digilent at the academic price.  This discount
  will only apply to people who are attending the class regularly and is on 
 a case-by-case basis from Digilent.\n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of 
 donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this
  class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, a
 nd this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
