CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/third-baltimore-hackathon-tickets-
 13312276377?aff=unallocated\n\nWhat is the Baltimore Hackathon?\n\nThe Balt
 imore Hackathon is a weekend event of social productivity (Think hacking th
 ings together\, not maliciously hacking a computer).  The goal is to bring 
 the community together to work on technical and creative projects and recog
 nize the best teams and projects with awards.  The judges will be composed 
 of representatives from the hackerspaces and makerspaces of Baltimore City.
 \n\nUnallocated Space will be judging!\n\nWho can attend?\n\nThis event is 
 open to the public and anyone can attend: students\, tinkerers\, profession
 als\, and even those that are just curious!  Tickets are not required to ch
 eck the event out just for an hour or so\, however leave the food\, seats\,
  and tables to the competitors.\n\nWhat’s included with a ticket?\n\nA $15 
 ticket includes an official Baltimore Hackathon T-shirt\, the opportunity t
 o present at the finale to compete for prizes\, and ideally food for the we
 ekend (depending on sponsorship).\n\nWhat are the prizes?\n\nPrize amounts 
 could increase depending on sponsorship\, initial prizes are listed below:\
 n\n$100 - Best Individual Software Project\n$300 - Best Team Software Proje
 ct\n$100 - Best Individual Hardware Project\n$300 - Best Team Hardware Proj
 ect\n$200 - Audience Favorite\n\nHow will the prizes be judged?\n\nCompetit
 ors must create a presentation from a mandatory template that will be provi
 ded at the start of the competition.  In the presentation\, they must descr
 ibe the motivation and methods for their project\, outcomes so far\, and th
 eir plans for future work.  Selected judges will make the final award decis
 ions based on project implementation and technical merit.\n\nWho will be ju
 dging?\n\nA representative from Unallocated Space and others within the Bal
 timore hackerspaces / makerspace community will be attending this event to 
 act as judges. Judging will take place on Sunday Nov\, 16th.\n\nWhen and wh
 ere?\n\nNovember 14th-16th at Advertising.com Inc\, 1020 Hull St\, Baltimor
 e\, MD 21230\n\n2012 Photos\n\nhttps://facebook.com/michael.rosner/albums/1
 0150850259776097/?refid=17&ref=bookmark\nhttps://facebook.com/michael.rosne
 r/albums/10150850256721097/?refid=17&ref=bookmark\n\n2012 Articles\n\nhttp:
 //www.examiner.com/article/inside-the-baltimore-hackathon\nhttp://www.csee.
 umbc.edu/2012/06/ahmad-abbas-takes-home-diyhacker-prize-at-baltimore-hackat
 hon/\n\n2010 Photos\n\nhttps://www.flickr.com/photos/baltimorehackathon/\n\
 n2010 Articles\n\nhttp://technical.ly/baltimore/2010/11/24/our-coverage-fro
 m-the-baltimore-hackathon/\nhttp://whatweekly.com/2010/12/02/hackathon/#.Ub
 teYhVgZQ8\n \nHave questions about Third Baltimore Hackathon?\n\nhttp://bal
 timorehackathon.com/
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:1020 Hull St \nBaltimore\, MD 21230
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:TENTATIVE
SUMMARY:Baltimore Hackathon
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
