UID:nmr9msqbr1468u80gped2chg9o@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130813T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will continue working on sending data from the FPGA to a lap
 top.\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx ISE installed.  Please ensur
 e you already have the ISE installed!!  We will not have time to wait for t
 he install process to complete (it usually takes 15-30 minutes).  Check out
  http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downlo
 adNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Suite for your OS.\n2. 
 Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA development board (must be Xilinx!!).
   We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. USB cable for your FPGA dev 
 board.\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\, we will not have extras.
   If you have questions about what board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallo
 catedspace.org.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would like to
  mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no me
 ans a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free
  to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20130820T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20130820T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:nmr9msqbr1468u80gped2chg9o@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20130820T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will continue working with Serial/EPP data transfers.  Here 
 are the goals based on dev board type:\n\n     Mojo:\n          1. Create a
  FIFO to buffer data being written to the serial (from FPGA to computer)\n 
          2. Write data as quickly as possible to the FIFO until it is full\
 , then wait for the FIFO to become empty and then add more data (most likel
 y a counter)\n          3. Implement a FIFO for input data buffering.\n\n  
    Basys:\n          1. Create a RAM block to store X registers of data.\n 
          2. Read and write data to and from these registers.\n          3. 
 Create 'op codes' that can be stored in the first register that will then c
 ause operations on other registers.  Also set a register to be a flag for a
 n operation being complete.  Example: Put 0x01 in register 2. 0x02 in regis
 ter 3\, then 0xff in register 1 (0xff being the flag for addition).  When r
 egister 4 is non-zero\, then the addition is complete.\n\nThis class is clo
 sed to new members.  If you already know VHDL and have a Basys or Mojo base
 d board\, please contact fpga@unallocatedspace.org to get into the class.  
 We are currently to far along in the class for new folks to join without pr
 ior knowledge of VHDL :(\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we woul
 d like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is
  by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 
 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
