DESCRIPTION:We will be going over how to make an FPGA drive an LCD monitor.
   With any luck I will have DB15 (VGA) breakout cables made before class.  
 For those of you who need a breakout cable\, please let me know as soon as 
 possible.\n\nIf you have a monitor with VGA connectors and can bring it\, p
 lease do.  We do have many monitors\, but with the extra people coming\, I'
 m not sure we'll have enough.\n\n\nRequired Items:\n1. Laptop with Xilinx I
 SE installed.  Please ensure you already have the ISE installed!!  We will 
 not have time to wait for the install process to complete (it usually takes
  15-30 minutes).  Check out http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.ht
 ml/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Des
 ign Suite for your OS.\n2. Some Xilinx Spartan 3 or greater FPGA developmen
 t board (must be Xilinx!!).  We prefer the Mojo or Digilent Basys II.\n3. U
 SB cable for your FPGA dev board.\n\nProvided Items:\n1. VGA breakout (if n
 eeded)\n2. LCD Monitor (1 per person up to ~ 7)\n\nBecause of the cost of F
 PGA dev boards\, we will not have extras.  If you have questions about what
  board to get\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nSince the space
  runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended dona
 tion for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to 
 the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
