DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:o0aab9lofngaokgu47b9rei7c8@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Charlie requested this be added\n\nOn the third weekend in Octo
 ber\, 1 million Scouts from 150 different countries will unite to celebrate
  the global power of Scouting.\nAnd they’ll do it without leaving the neigh
 borhood.\nJoin the fun by involving your pack\, troop\, team\, post\, ship 
 or crew in the 2016 Jamboree-on-the-Air and Jamboree-on-the-Internet — held
  concurrently Oct. 14 to 16\, 2016.\nThis year’s theme — “Discover Our Worl
 d” — challenges young men and young women to reach out to their fellow Scou
 ts and learn about the differences and similarities that unite us as member
 s of World Scouting.\nThe conversation topics are limitless: What’s the Eag
 le Scout equivalent in Ecuador? Where do Scouts from Helsinki hike? Do Dutc
 h Scouts ever use Dutch ovens?\nThe 59-year-old Jamboree-on-the-Air uses am
 ateur radio to enable the exchange of questions like those. To participate\
 , most units visit an amateur radio operator’s ham shack or ask the radio o
 perator to set up at a local park.\nThe smaller Jamboree-on-the-Internet is
  20 years old and requires less setup. Scouts or Venturers use any internet
 -enabled device —  computer\, laptop\, tablet or smartphone — to talk to Sc
 outs from far-off places.\nIn addition to being incredibly fun\, JOTA and J
 OTI count toward Scouting requirements:\nFor Tigers\, this meets requiremen
 ts for the elective adventure Family Stories.\nFor Webelos\, it counts towa
 rd the Arrow of Light adventure Building a Better World.\nBoy Scouts can ch
 eck off a requirement for the Citizenship in the World merit badge.\nAll Cu
 b Scouts\, Boy Scouts\, Varsity Scouts\, Venturers and adult leaders can co
 unt the event toward the requirements for the International Spirit Award.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Jamboree-on-the-Air
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
