DESCRIPTION:Arduino Night Starting Over (10 May 7-10PM)\n\nArduino Night ha
 s come a long way over the last few months.  Far enough that it's becoming 
 difficult for new people to join in on the festivities.  That means that it
 's time to start everything over again :D\n\nAgenda:\n\n1. Get everyone set
  up with the Arduino IDE\n2. What is an Arduino\n3. Upload "Hello World" pr
 ogram (using Serial)\n4. Blink an LED\n5. Fade an LED\n\nRequired Items:\n\
 n1. Laptop\n2. Arduino (Mega\, Duemilanove\, Due\, Boarduino\, or UNO)\n3. 
 USB cable for your Arduino\n4. Breadboard (small or large)\n5. Jumper wires
 \n\nIf you need any items in the required items section\, please E-Mail uas
 .arduino@gmail.com.  We have a few of all of the required items\, but we ne
 ed to know how many to prepare.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, 
 we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $1
 0. It is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this cla
 ss\, is 100% free to all!
