DESCRIPTION:This will be a different format than last time. This week will 
 be the "Arduino Challenge". The basic idea is that I will list several simp
 le to mildly challenging things to do with your Arduino. All challenges wil
 l use things that we have covered (successfully) at least once. I will not 
 divulge the details of the challenge until Friday night.\n\nOne other note:
  I will be there to help out people who get stuck. I will not give the answ
 er\, but will do my best to guide folks in the right direction :)\n\nRequir
 ed Items:\n1. Laptop\n2. Arduino (Uno or better)\n3. USB cable for Arduino\
 n4. Breadboard (full height if possible)\n5. Jumper leads for breadboard\n\
 nOptional Items (please bring the following if you can):\n1. 9V battery\n2.
  Aligator clips\n\nIf you need any items in the required items section\, pl
 ease E-Mail uas.arduino@gmail.com. We have a few of all of the required ite
 ms\, but we need to know how many to prepare.\n\nSince the space runs off o
 f donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation for th
 is class is $10. It is by no means a requirement! Attendance to the space\,
  and this class\, is 100% free to all!
