DTEND:20170718T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:ormoansd427l5dmsk7i64akedg@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:**This class is a trial run for a future class. If you attend p
 lease be prepared to provide the instructor with constructive feedback.**\n
 \nPurpose\nFacilitate a distro-agnostic understanding of linux systems.\nTo
  introduce tools and critical methods for performing a wide range of tasks.
 \nEnable students to better solve their own problems.\n\nSkill Level:\nThis
  is a rigorous entry-level or intermediate course. If you have never used t
 he shell before\, you are encouraged to spend 1 hour on:\nCode Academy: Lea
 rn the command line to learn the basic navigation skills you’ll need to flo
 w through the class.\n\nFormat\nThis course is an instructor led course hea
 vy in hands-on activities with an element of ctf-style gamification. The co
 urse is currently 8 sessions long and ends in a capstone project. The class
  is designed to be 60/40 with theory and hands-on exercises.\n\nGenerally w
 e’ll cover one topic\, I’ll open up the exercises and we’ll move on.\n\nEqu
 ipment\nYou will need to bring a laptop or mobile device that can run a web
  browser. The class will be taught using virtual machines which students wi
 ll register at the beginning of the class. A keyboard is encouraged\n\n(opt
 ional)\nThough you only need a browser\, you’ll enjoy yourself more if you 
 install an ssh client such as:\npuTTY tray or cygwin on windows\njuicessh o
 n android\nserverauditor on IOS\ndefault ssh client on MacOS / Linux.\n\nIn
 structor Note\nHey I’m Flay. I’ve been a native linux user for years and ha
 ve spent hundreds of hours in research and experimentation developing this 
 class and its exercises. It may never be finished\, but it is my sincere ho
 pe to help you reach your own linux goals through this class.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Linux 102 Test Run
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20140419T230000Z
DTEND:20140420T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:ouabgtdmk06hor1vdvf6bdrt0c@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Rumor has it\, energy drinks will be provided! Maybe prizes too
 ? We're\nkind'a flying from the seat of our pants with this first Hackathon
 .\nBut its sure to be fun!\n\nHow do you participate?\nShow up with the dev
  environment of your choice. Form a team of 1-2\npeople (preferably two).\n
 \nThere will be 3 rounds. Each round the judges will provide a\nprogramming
  problem. These problems may be something like Talk like a\nPirate day cont
 est\, it may be an irc bot\, a Space Improvement code\, or\nobscure protoco
 l.\n\nPrograms can be written in any language\, but must work on a judges\n
 Unix or Windows VM (distro\, version\, and patch level of each OS will\nbe 
 announced at the beginning of each round\, and may change throughout\nthe n
 ight).\n\nOnce you think your code is done\, submit the code to the judges 
 via\nany means the judges can successfully retrieve (USB\, ftp\, fileshare\
 ,\ngithub\, bitbucket...).\n\nCode will be tested in the order it's downloa
 ded (hint: local FTP may\nbe faster than github)\n\nIf your code fails to c
 ompile\, you take a drink and lose a point.\nIf your code compiles\, but fa
 ils to run\, you take a drink and lose a point.\nIf your code runs\, but fa
 ils to produce the correct output\, you take a\ndrink and lose a point.\nTh
 e first team to successfully produce the right output gets 3 points.\nEvery
 one still working drinks.\nThe second team to successfully produce the righ
 t output gets 2\npoints. Everyone still working drinks.\nThe third team to 
 successfully produce the right output gets 1 point.\nEveryone still working
  drinks AND a new round begins.\n\nThe first three successful programs for 
 each round will be showcased\non UAS's github.\n\nNote: the word "drink" re
 lates to liquid substance of the developers\nchoice as allowed by UAS\, and
  does not imply any bias or promotion.\n\nDon't feel like writing code? Do 
 you just want to hang out and watch\nyour friends (or complete strangers) t
 ry to program and drink at the\nsame time? Do you want to make their lives 
 even more difficult? Then\nwe invite you to join Team Distraction!\n\nVolun
 teers: We'll need about 2-3 judges\, and we'll need ideas for\nprogramming 
 problems\, so feel free to submit them!\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UAS Monthly Hackathon (Cancelled until TBA)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
