RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20150213T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We are getting back to LCDs this week.  The last time we dealt 
 with a 16x2 display\, we used the LiquidCrystal library.  This time we are 
 going to 'bit bang' the LCD by hand.  The idea is to learn how to control e
 xternal devices for which you don't have a library.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Wir
 ing up the 16x2 LCD\n     2. Quick look at the datasheet\n     3. Explain h
 ow the various commands work\n     4. Create code to initialize the display
  and show a blinking cursor\n     5. Create code to display 'Hello World'\n
      6. Time permitting:\n          a. Moving the cursor\n          b. Addi
 ng custom characters\n\n     \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E
 -Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to the Google Hangou
 t.  The hangout will generally be started just before class (6:45-7:15 PM).
   If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, please E-Mail arduino@unallocateds
 pace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can be found 
 at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=
 sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three days before a clas
 s.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, M
 ega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board does not have U
 SB programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\,
  Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the
  long one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are okay for now)\
 n     4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop with th
 e Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires fo
 r your breadboard\n     7. 16x2 LCD (E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org if
  you need one to use for class)\n     8. Variable resistor (potentiometer) 
 for setting the contrast\n\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. 16x2 LCD if needed\n
      2. Variable resistor if needed\n     \n\nSince Unallocated Space runs 
 off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donation f
 or this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it does help us 
 keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% fre
 e to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
