DESCRIPTION:Sunday March 2nd (think of it as extended leap year day) from 6
 pm to 9pm\n\nThis month's focus: Red Team\nThis month's competition: http:/
 /bostonkeyparty.net/\n\nForgotten will be discussing an opportunity for Una
 llocated Space to\ninteract with this year's Collegiate Cyber Defense Compe
 tition (CCDC)\nregional tournament. The CCDC a Congressionally recognized c
 ompetition\nthat offers college students an excellent opportunity to practi
 ce\nincident response skills as teams are assessed based on their ability\n
 to detect and respond to outside threats\, maintain availability of\nexisti
 ng services\, respond to business requests\, and balance security\nneeds ag
 ainst business needs.\n\nGomi will be going over the hows and whys of exten
 ding John the\nRipper. Resources:\nhttps://github.com/maetrics/gomi-scripts
 /tree/master/john\nGomi will also be going over Boston Key Party CTF challe
 nges.\n\nHal from Digital Intercept\, a local CTF team\, will be discussing
  his\nexperiences with CTFs.
