UID:qll6litv92d3n57lpm0t6af474@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Ever wanted to send the interesting data your Arduino is collec
 ting back to a PC to do long term storage and analysis?\n\nEver wanted to c
 ontrol your project without pushing buttons on a shield?\n\nEver wanted to 
 talk to your Arduino?\n\nEver wanted it to talk back?\n\nEver wish Pyr0 wou
 ld have given the presentation the first time?\n\nWell if you answered yes 
 to any of these questions\, and promise to not pelt me with Nerf darts and 
 Snort pigs\, then come on down to Serial communication with the Arduino Rou
 nd 2\; FIGHT!\n\n :Basic Topics:\nBytes vs Strings\nSending multiple values
  to the PC\nReceiving multiple values from the PC\nActuating a pin remotely
 \n\n :Advanced Topics:\nSending and receiving variable length values\nDevel
 oping a simple communication protocol\n\nFor this class we will be using Pr
 ocessing on the PC. Please goto https://processing.org/download/ and downlo
 ad your OS specific version\, 32bit preferred. Don't worry all Processing c
 ode will be provided in it's entirety. For those interested at the end of t
 he class I will dissect the processing code and give a detailed explanation
  of what is going on. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino serial data
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
