BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20141003T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20141003T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:r6utgh0vigic1fthu1bcjpgo9g@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20141003T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be fading LEDs with PWM\, learning how to use for loops
 \, creating variables\, bit shifting\, and reading analog values.  \n\nAgen
 da:\n     1. Pulse width modulation\n     2. Create sketch to turn LED part
  on\n     3. Play with this sketch to make the LED dimmer or brighter\n    
  4. Intro to conditional loops (for)\n     5. Use a for loop to ramp up LED
  brightness\n     6. Change sketch to ramp up\, then down\n     7. Explanat
 ion of how potentiometers work\n     8. Create sketch that changes LED brig
 htness based on analog value from potentiometer\n\n     \nIf you cannot att
 end the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be
  added to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will be started just before clas
 s (6:45-7:00 PM).\n\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can
  be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMW
 FXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three days bef
 ore a class.\n\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (U
 no\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board doe
 s not have USB programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, 
 Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Bre
 adboard (the long one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are ok
 ay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. La
 ptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jum
 per wires for your breadboard\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Breadboard and ju
 mpers (if you don't have any of either)\n     2. LEDs\n     3. Resistors (2
 00-1\,000 Ohm)\n     4. Potentiometer (2 KOhm)\n\nSince Unallocated Space r
 uns off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommended donati
 on for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it does help
  us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100%
  free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20141017T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20141017T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:r6utgh0vigic1fthu1bcjpgo9g@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20141017T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be using push buttons to change the brightness of an LE
 D one step at a time.  During the course of this little project\, we will a
 lso cover de-bouncing buttons.  If time permits\, we will start with Serial
  communications.  \n\nAgenda:\n     1.  How push buttons work\n     2.  How
  to connect the buttons\n     3.  Reading push button values\n     4.  De-b
 ouncing the input\n     5.  Incrementing/Decrementing the LED value\n     6
 .  Time permitting - Sending serial from the Arduino to the computer\n\n   
   \nIf you cannot attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedsp
 ace.org and ask to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will be sta
 rted just before class (6:45-7:00 PM).\n\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and
  previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0B
 zpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made duri
 ng the three days before a class.\n\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino 
 board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n    
  2. If your board does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a 
 programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduin
 o\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small s
 quare-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or p
 rogrammer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\,
  or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard\n\nProvided Items:\n    
  1. Breadboard and jumpers (if you don't have any of either)\n     2. LEDs\
 n     3. Resistors (200-1\,000 Ohm)\n     4. Push button\n\nSince Unallocat
 ed Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommen
 ded donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\, but it
  does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and this class
 \, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
