DESCRIPTION:THIS CLASS STARTS AT 8\, NOT 7!!!!!\n\nIn the last class we wen
 t over the basics of serial communication.  This class will dive a little d
 eeper into serial by using Python to talk to the Arduino instead of the Ard
 uino IDE's serial monitor.  This will enable the sending of more complicate
 d data than just ASCII strings.  \n\nThis means that everyone will need to 
 have Python 2.7 and pyserial installed.  Please see the pyserial page to do
 wnload and install pyserial after installing Python.  For those on Linux\, 
 you should be able to install both from your package manager.  Feel free to
  E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org if you have questions about how to ins
 tall Python or pyserial.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Using the Python interactive s
 hell\n     2. Connecting to the Arduino\n     3. Sending and receiving data
 \n     4. Create an echo sketch\n     5. Create an LED dimming sketch\n    
  6. Create sketch to read analog values\n\nIf you cannot attend the class i
 n person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and ask to be added to the G
 oogle Hangout. The hangout will generally be started just before class (7:4
 5-8:15 PM). If you do not have an invite by 8:15\, please E-Mail arduino@un
 allocatedspace.org.\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous classes can b
 e found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFX
 X0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three days befor
 e a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino board of some kind (Uno\,
  Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n     2. If your board does no
 t have USB programming built in\, you will need a programmer (AVRISP\, Bus 
 Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Arduino\, etc)\n     3. Breadbo
 ard (the long one if possible\, though the small square-ish ones are okay f
 or now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or programmer\n     5. Laptop
  with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\, or Mac)\n     6. Jumper 
 wires for your breadboard\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. Breadboard and jumper
 s (if you don't have any of either)\n     2. LEDs\n     3. Resistors (200-1
 \,000 Ohm)\n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like
  to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no
  means a requirement\, but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance 
 to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
