CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We will be creating a function generator out of an Arduino.  We
  will focus on sine waves\, but sawtooth isn't much different.  \n\nIf you 
 have an oscilloscope\, please bring it!  I will be bringing one with two ch
 annels\, and the space has one with two channels.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. How a
 nalog to digital conversion (ADC) works\n     2. How digital to analog conv
 ersion (DAC) works\n     3. DAC using PWM\n     4. Creating a sine wave on 
 the fly\n     5. Pre-computing a sine wave\n     6. R2R ladder\n     7. Tim
 e permitting:\n               Direct port manipulation\n\n     \nIf you can
 not attend the class in person\, E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org and as
 k to be added to the Google Hangout.  The hangout will generally be started
  just before class (6:45-7:15 PM).  If you do not have an invite by 7:15\, 
 please E-Mail arduino@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nThe slides for the upcoming 
 and previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id
 =0BzpbYvv0G2kMTURwUVhhMWFXX0k&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made d
 uring the three days before a class.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. An Arduino
  board of some kind (Uno\, Due\, Mega\, Boarduino\, Duemilanove\, etc)\n   
   2. If your board does not have USB programming built in\, you will need a
  programmer (AVRISP\, Bus Pirate\, Bus Blaster\, AVR Dragon\, another Ardui
 no\, etc)\n     3. Breadboard (the long one if possible\, though the small 
 square-ish ones are okay for now)\n     4. USB cable for your board and/or 
 programmer\n     5. Laptop with the Arduino IDE installed (Linux\, Windows\
 , or Mac)\n     6. Jumper wires for your breadboard\n     7. 10 - 100-300 O
 hm resistors and 10 more of twice that value (there will be a lot of resist
 ors available)\n     8. Variable resistor (potentiometer)\n\nProvided Items
 :\n     1. Resistors\, potentiometers\, and capacitors as needed\n\nSince U
 nallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the 
 recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement\
 , but it does help us keep the lights on!  Attendance to the space\, and th
 is class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
