UID:rkn9a79egr8ke9dlr8pu1ss6mg@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:TOPIC: Working Group-Build a better Kali Kick Off\nSUMMARY: Kal
 i Linux is like that Swiss Army Knife that everyone has with 127 tools on i
 t.\nSome tools are used more often and for the most part the rest of it is 
 just bloat and goes\nunused. I am not saying Kali is unusable and is terrib
 le\, but wouldn&#39\;t it be nice to have your own\nbuild that is suited fo
 r you and updates and builds things the way you like every time. No\nmatter
  what you do Blue Team or Red Team you have your go to tools and developmen
 t\nenvironments. I want to start building scripts and use Dave Kennedy’s Pe
 n Testers Framework\n(PTF) to create something people can use to deploy the
 ir own environment.\nI want to start building this idea and over time we ma
 ke it better and better. We will all\ncode/script and contribute to the end
  goal. We all have our specialty: Wireless\, Defense\,\nPentesting\, Compli
 ance\, Forensics\, HAM\, and a few more.\nThis is a group effort. I will no
 t be telling you what to type into your computer to create this. We\nare al
 l creating together. We will step outside our comfort zone together and lea
 rn and grow as\nINFOSEC professionals. This will be an on going Work Group 
 that will meet on a as needed\nand hopefully frequent basis to meet our goa
 l.\nGOAL:\nCreate custom script/framework that we can deploy on boxes for o
 ur RED/BLUE needs. Have it\non Github to share and work together. If it tak
 es 4 repos to make different builds then so be it.\nWe are not gonna be per
 fect but we can get pretty damn close. Maybe\nThings to bring:\nLaptop\nGit
 hub account\nIdeas to make a custom RED/BLUE OS\n\nHomework:\nDownload and 
 check out Dave Kennedy’s PTF\nhttps://github.com/trustedsec/ptf\nList the t
 ools you use and like and their pre reqs.\nSKILL LEVEL: Everyone\nPRESENTER
 : Wasabi\n\nhttps://www.meetup.com/Unallocated-Space/events/241976961/
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:InfoSec Night: Working Group-Build a better Kali Kick Off
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
