UID:s2tn4bob2trrccnjvhum1t78d4@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:This Arduino Night will focus on code more than hardware.  Don'
 t worry if you are a slow typist or don't know much C/C++.  I will be posti
 ng the code to Pastebin for everyone to access.\n\nAgenda:\n1. Mapping valu
 es (convert a 10 bit value to an 8 bit value)\n2. Timers (Schedule somethin
 g to happen every x us/ms/s\n3. Buttons (Needed to play with interrupts)\n3
 . Interrupts (Ensure certain code runs when certain events happen)\n4. Bit 
 masking and shifting (Needed for using PORTX registers)\n5. PORTX registers
  (Writing directly to the registers without digitalWrite())\n\nRequired Ite
 ms:\n1. Laptop\n2. Arduino (Mega\, Uno\, or Duemilanove )\n3. USB cable for
  Arduino\n4. Breadboard & wires\n\nProvided Items:\n1. LEDs\n2. Tactile swi
 tches\n\nIf you need any items in the required items section\, please E-Mai
 l uas.arduino@gmail.com. We have a few of all of the required items\, but w
 e need to know how many to prepare.\nSince the space runs off of donations\
 , we would like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is 
 $10. It is by no means a requirement! Attendance to the space\, and this cl
 ass\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20140126T230000Z
DTEND:20140127T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:s7a10h38g1fsq449dcpi3dapn8@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Subject: Forensics\n\nWhy forensics? Often\, when I talk about 
 CTFs to people\, they picture it being solely about exploiting boxes at Def
 con. While exploiting is indeed a flashy part of CTFs\, it is only a portio
 n of the skills used to qualify or compete in a CTF.\n\nThis month's meetin
 g is to inform/remind people that there are other aspects involved. Cryptog
 raphy\, recon\, reverse engineering\, network and web exploitation\, and fo
 rensics!\n\nChallenge of the month is http://computer-forensics.sans.org/bl
 og/2014/01/10/deadline-approaching-apt-malware-and-memory-challenge-dfircon
 \n\nAnswer three out of five questions of this memory dump\, and you can po
 ssibly win a free SANS Simulcast class!!!\n\nAt the meeting I'll be going o
 f the tools and techniques I used to answer the question. Unless I fail at 
 it\, which in that case I'm going to give a demo on using Mandiant Redline 
 to perform forensics in an incident response capacity.\n\nAlso\, feel free 
 to meet other people interested in competing in CTF. Form teams\, or recrui
 t.\n\n-gomi 
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CTF Meeting: Forensics
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
