DESCRIPTION:To participate in the AC portion of Electronics Fundamentals yo
 u will need some sort of function generator (also known as a signal generat
 or) capable of going from about 1Hz ~ 1MHz. You can either buy a prebuilt o
 ne (those are costly\, but you get what you pay for) or you can build a sim
 ple one from a kit.\nThese are the kits I recommend: \nhttp://smile.amazon.
 com/Elenco-1MHz-Function-Generator-Kit/dp/B0002MQEW4/ref=sr_1_5?ie=UTF8&qid
 =1451359945&sr=8-5&keywords=function+generator\n\nhttp://smile.amazon.com/F
 unction-Generator-DIY-Tech-FG085/dp/B00C5UO8U6/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&qid=14513
 59945&sr=8-2&keywords=function+generator\n\nThis night will be dedicated to
  building and learning how to use the function generator. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD\, United Sta
 tes
