CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Signups will be up within the next day or two.\n\nThe Metasploi
 t Framework is a must-have tool for penetration testers. Armitage builds a 
 workflow on top of the Metasploit Framework and exposes its most advanced c
 apabilities. Cobalt Strike augments Armitage with tools to carry out social
  engineering attacks. This lab oriented class will introduce you to the pen
 etration testing process from the perspectives of Armitage and Cobalt Strik
 e.\n\nYou'll learn how to:\n\n* Choose the right remote or client-side expl
 oit\n* Attack with features\n* Launch a spear phishing attack\n* Control a 
 compromised system\n\nWhere to learn more:\n\nArmitage http://www.fastandea
 syhacking.com\nCobalt Strike http://www.advancedpentest.com\n\nStudent Requ
 irements:\n\nTo participate in the labs\, you must have VMWare Player\, VMW
 are Fusion\, or VMWare Workstation installed. VirtualBox is not supported. 
 Your laptop should have a DVD drive and 14GB free disk space for three virt
 ual machines\, provided by the instructor. Your laptop should also have eno
 ugh RAM (2GB min\, 4GB recommended) to run two virtual machines at the same
  time.\nYou should be familiar with how to work on the command line in eith
 er Linux or Windows. This course does not assume familiarity with the Metas
 ploit Framework.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Armitage/Cobalt Strike Class with Raphael Mudge
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
