UID:tvqgsut871o31f1m3eh3rp37js@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:This will be the first installment of the FPGA classes.  The on
 ly hardware requirement is that you have a Xilinx based Spartan 3 or greate
 r (Virtex is okay as well).  Spartan 2 will not be used because it requires
  a very old version of the Xilinx ISE.\n\nAgenda:\n\n1. Introductions\n2. C
 onfigure Xilinx ISE web kit software\n3. Comparison of FPGA and traditional
  microcontrollers\n4. Explanation of UCF files\n5. Uploading a "Hello World
 " program (code is provided)\n6. Explain how the hello world program works\
 n7. Modify the hello world program to blink at a different rate\n\nRequired
  Items:\n\n1. Xilinx based Spartan 3 or higher FPGA (Virtex works as well)\
 n2. Laptop running Windows or Linux (OSX will not work!)\n3. Breadboard and
  LEDs if your FPGA board does not have LEDs\n4. Laptop must have ~ 30GB of 
 free disk space for Xilinx ISE\n\nBecause of the cost of FPGA dev boards\, 
 we will not have extras.  If you have questions about what board to get\, p
 lease E-Mail uas.arduino@gmail.com (no need to make an uas.fpga@gmail.com!)
 \n\nPlease download the Xilinx ISE web kit from http://www.xilinx.com/suppo
 rt/download/index.htm.  The section you will want to download from is "Viva
 do Design Suite - 2013.1 Full Product Installation"  We will work out the l
 icensing in class.\n\nSince the space runs off of donations\, we would like
  to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $10. It is by n
 o means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% 
 free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Dev Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
