UID:u7ginldaif54deucl91mr4u2pc@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Possibly SRAM\, and just general messing around.\n\nAgenda\n\n1
 . Reading and writing to SRAM (we will be using 256K CY7C199CN chips.\n2. T
 ransistors (should have done this at the last class). Using them to turn on
  LEDs and DC motors.\n3. Two way communication to the Arduino using Serial.
 read() and Serial.println().\n4. Using tactile switches (tiny buttons) to t
 oggle two LEDs.\n\nRequired Items:\n\n1. Arduino (Uno or better)\n2. Laptop
  (needs to have the Arduino software loaded)\n3. Breadboard\n4. Jumper wire
 s. Full size is best\, but small ones will work as well.\n\nProvided Items:
 \n\n1. 2N2222 Transistors (Datasheet)\n2. CY7C199CN 256K SRAM (Datasheet)\n
 3. DC motors\n4. LEDs\n5. Tactile switches\n\nIf there are any questions\, 
 comments\, suggestions\, etc then please contact Proto17 at dmp250net@gmail
 .com.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arduino Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
