UID:vmo4db7tguifncajb1v2d2bfeo@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20140902T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:We stopped short last class and will be picking up at displayin
 g analog values from the ADC on VGA monitors.  Once that is complete\,we wi
 ll begin work (might not finish) on sampling audio with the ADC\, and then 
 outputting that same audio with a 1 bit Sigma Delta Digital to Analog Conve
 rter (DAC) courtesy of Martin.  We will not go into the 1 bit DAC this clas
 s\, and instead will just be using it much like an IP Core. \n\nFor this cl
 ass\, if you have a male to male headphone cable\, please bring it!  Also\,
  you will need to bring your own headphones.  They should be the in ear typ
 e since there is not much power coming from the FPGA.  If you do not have t
 he in ear type\, you can also use powered portable speakers.\n\nAgenda:\n  
    1. Overview of last class\n     2. Display vertical bar that moves based
  on ADC samples\n     3. Each person will modify the code to draw a horizon
 tal bar\n     4. Explanation of audio sampling design\n     5. Go over circ
 uit design for design\n     6. Add in Sigma Delta code\n     7. Wire up cir
 cuit with cell phone or computer headphones as input\, and listen to the ou
 tput\n     8. Experiment with the filter and DC bias\n\nFor those of you wi
 th a Nexys3\, Basys2\, or Atlys\, you will be able to connect a VGA cable d
 irectly.  For those using a Mojo or some other board without a VGA connecti
 on\, please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org stating that you need a VGA br
 eakout cable!  There are several breakout cables from last class\, but we n
 eed to make sure there are enough on hand.\n     \nIf you would like to joi
 n the class\, then please E-Mail fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n  The class is
  now to a point where you need to know VHDL prior to \njoining.  We also st
 ream the class on Google Hangouts (no prior knowledge to join the hangout).
   Please send an \nE-Mail to fpga@unallocatedspace.org if you would like to
  join the Google Hangout.\n\n\nThe slides for the upcoming and previous cla
 sses can be found at https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbG
 NiRVRBUFN4cWs&usp=sharing.  The slides are generally made during the three 
 days before a class.\n\n**IMPORTANT** You *MUST* have ISE (not Vivado!) ins
 talled prior to the start of class!!!  ISE can take upwards of 30 minutes t
 o an hour to install.  We will not have time to wait for ISE to be installe
 d.  Please go to http://www.xilinx.com/support/download/index.html/content/
 xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and download the ISE Design Suite p
 ackage for your operating system.  If you have licensing or installation is
 sues\, please contact fpga@unallocatedspace.org.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1
 . FPGA development board with Spartan 3 or Spartan 6\n     2. USB cable for
  programming\n     3. JTAG programmer if your board does not have USB\n    
  4. Laptop **with ISE installed** and either wired or wireless network conn
 ectivity\n     5. VGA breakout (red\, green\, blue\, horizontal sync\, vert
 ical sync\, and ground) if you do not have a VGA connector on your dev boar
 d.\n     6. Breadboard\n     7. In ear headphones (or amplified portable sp
 eakers)\n     8. Male to male headphone cable\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. V
 GA breakout if you let the instructor know\n     2. MCP3001\n     3. Variab
 le resistors (1K and 10K)\n     4. Jumpers (x12)\n     5. Capacitors (2x 47
 nF\, 1x 100nF)\n     6. Resistors ( 2x >= 200 Ohm)\n\nWe have been given 'a
 cademic' status from Digilent Inc (http://www.digilentinc.com).  This means
  that the instructor can (sometimes) purchase boards from Digilent at the a
 cademic price.  This discount will only apply to people who are attending t
 he class regularly and is on a case-by-case basis from Digilent.\n\nSince U
 nallocated Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the 
 recommended donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!
   Attendance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
