UID:vmo4db7tguifncajb1v2d2bfeo@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20141028T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Last week was the end of the serial UART classes.  This week we
  will take a look at the Xilinx DDS (Direct Digital Synthesizer) IP Core.  
 We will be using it to generate a sine wave that will then be output via bo
 th a resistor ladder (R2R ladder) and a sigma delta DAC (Digital to Analog 
 Converter).\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Overview of last class\n     2. Intro to th
 e Xilinx DDS Core\n     3. Create a sine wave generator\n     4. Explain an
 d wire up an R2R ladder\n     5. Add code to the module to output a sine wa
 ve to R2R ladder\n     6. Verify sine wave with o'scope or headphones\n    
  7. Modify the design to use a sigma delta DAC\n     8. Verify again\n\n   
   \nIf you would like to join the class\, then please E-Mail fpga@unallocat
 edspace.org.\n  The class is now to a point where you need to know VHDL pri
 or to \njoining.  We also stream the class on Google Hangouts (no prior kno
 wledge required to join the hangout).  Please send an \nE-Mail to fpga@unal
 locatedspace.org if you would like to join the Google Hangout.\n\n\nThe sli
 des for the upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://drive.goo
 gle.com/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbGNiRVRBUFN4cWs&usp=sharing.  The slides
  are generally made during the three days before a class.\n\n**IMPORTANT** 
 You *MUST* have ISE (not Vivado!) installed prior to the start of class!!! 
  ISE can take upwards of 30 minutes to an hour to install.  We will not hav
 e time to wait for ISE to be installed.  Please go to http://www.xilinx.com
 /support/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.htm
 l and download the ISE Design Suite package for your operating system.  If 
 you have licensing or installation issues\, please contact fpga@unallocated
 space.org.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. FPGA development board with Spartan 
 3 or Spartan 6\n     2. USB cable for programming\n     3. JTAG programmer 
 if your board does not have USB\n     4. Laptop **with ISE installed** and 
 either wired or wireless network connectivity\n     5. Breadboard with jump
 ers\n\n\nWe have been given 'academic' status from Digilent Inc (http://www
 .digilentinc.com).  This means that the instructor can (sometimes) purchase
  boards from Digilent at the academic price.  This discount will only apply
  to people who are attending the class regularly and is on a case-by-case b
 asis from Digilent.\n\nSince Unallocated Space runs off of donations\, we w
 ould like to mention that the recommended donation for this class is $5. It
  is by no means a requirement!  Attendance to the space\, and this class\, 
 is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20141104T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20141104T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:vmo4db7tguifncajb1v2d2bfeo@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20141104T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Last week we created a sine wave the the DDS IP core from Xilin
 x and output it via an R2R ladder.  This week we will finish off the sine w
 ave experiment by outputting with a sigma delta converter.  Additionally\, 
 we will start working on a communications protocol over serial.  This will 
 make use of the serial UART we created earlier.  The goal is to design some
 thing that can withstand device resets.  This will eventually be used on th
 e FFT display project as the configuration/control method.  I do not expect
  to get all the way through the agenda.\n\nIf your laptop only has one avai
 lable USB port\, you will need to get an USB hub in the near future.  You w
 ill be using one USB connection for the FPGA\, and another for the USB to s
 erial converter.\n\nAgenda:\n     1. Overview of last class\n     2. Change
  existing sine wave generation code to use sigma delta\n     3. Output sine
  wave to o'scope\n     4. Create a new project for the serial UART controll
 er\n     5. Come up with a serial communications protocol\n     6. Write VH
 DL module for the protocol\n     7. Use a test bench to validate the design
 \n     8. Wire up the USB to serial converters and test with the FPGA\n\n  
    \nIf you would like to join the class\, then please E-Mail fpga@unalloca
 tedspace.org.  The class is now to a point where you need to know VHDL prio
 r to joining.  We also stream the class on Google Hangouts (no prior knowle
 dge required to join the hangout).  Please send an E-Mail to fpga@unallocat
 edspace.org if you would like to join the Google Hangout.\n\n\nThe slides f
 or the upcoming and previous classes can be found at https://drive.google.c
 om/folderview?id=0BzpbYvv0G2kMbGNiRVRBUFN4cWs&usp=sharing.  The slides are 
 generally made during the three days before a class.\n\n**IMPORTANT** You *
 MUST* have ISE (not Vivado!) installed prior to the start of class!!!  ISE 
 can take upwards of 30 minutes to an hour to install.  We will not have tim
 e to wait for ISE to be installed.  Please go to http://www.xilinx.com/supp
 ort/download/index.html/content/xilinx/en/downloadNav/design-tools.html and
  download the ISE Design Suite package for your operating system.  If you h
 ave licensing or installation issues\, please contact fpga@unallocatedspace
 .org.\n\nRequired Items:\n     1. FPGA development board with Spartan 3 or 
 Spartan 6\n     2. USB cable for programming\n     3. JTAG programmer if yo
 ur board does not have USB\n     4. Laptop **with ISE installed** and eithe
 r wired or wireless network connectivity\n     5. Breadboard with jumpers\n
      6. USB hub if needed\n\nProvided Items:\n     1. USB to serial convert
 er (http://www.amazon.com/dp/B009T2ZR6W/) \n\nWe have been given 'academic'
  status from Digilent Inc (http://www.digilentinc.com).  This means that th
 e instructor can (sometimes) purchase boards from Digilent at the academic 
 price.  This discount will only apply to people who are attending the class
  regularly and is on a case-by-case basis from Digilent.\n\nSince Unallocat
 ed Space runs off of donations\, we would like to mention that the recommen
 ded donation for this class is $5. It is by no means a requirement!  Attend
 ance to the space\, and this class\, is 100% free to all!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Shaw Court\, Severn\, MD\, United States
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FPGA Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
