DESCRIPTION:During this hacknight\, we'll give participants access to APIs 
 and toolkits provided by IOTA\, SIA\, Chain\, and Netki. Participants will 
 also be able to directly connect with developers from these companies throu
 gh BEN's Slack channel to get any questions they may have answered. I can w
 ork to organize mini workshops or collaboration challenges to add more educ
 ation and fun to the event.\n\nIf you have any ideas or input please forwar
 d them my way. Looking forward to the event.\n\nDescription: The Blockchain
  Education Network is hosting a global educational gauntlet which is a bloc
 kchain accelerator that shines a global spotlight on applications developed
  throughout November to get the mentor-ship participants need to take their
  ideas and projects to the next level. Get questions answered by blockchain
  developers and have your project reviewed by blockchain Venture Capitalist
 s. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Blockchain Education Network (BEN) Hack Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20130316T210000Z
DTEND:20130317T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:vrl2avsucpib5amdas6dk0fhd8@google.com
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Class requirments:\nBasic C or C++ knowledge\nComputer capable 
 of RDP (some will be provided if needed).\n \nWe'll be utilizing pre-made V
 Ms to do our work on\, if you wish to keep a copy of your VM we can export 
 it to self-brought USB media of your choice. Expected size ~20-30GB. (Win7/
 8 + Visual Studio + WDK). \nTopics to be covered include:\nWinDbg\nWindows 
 Driver development environment\nCompiling Windows Drivers\nWindows Driver M
 odel\nTypes of drivers in the Windows Operating System\nUser Mode vs Kernel
  Mode programming\nWhat NAUGHTY things can we do with windows drivers?\nHel
 lo world driver! or: it's really that easy?\n \nBonus topic:\nDefenses agai
 nst rouge drivers and how you can circumvent them the easy way and the hard
  way.\n \nFringe benefits of the class:\nUnderstanding how damn easy it is 
 to make a windows rootkit and yet how frustrating it is to get one that can
  be successfully deployed.
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:UAS
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Windows Driver Dev
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
