DESCRIPTION:Come out to Unallocated Space for the Software Defined Radio (S
 DR) Capture the Flag competition and cookout!\n \nWe will be having an info
 rmal CTF style final exam to test what you have learned in the “Introductio
 n to Signal Analysis” class. Everybody is welcome to participate!\n \nWe wi
 ll fire up the grill about 6pm and start serving burgers shortly after that
 . This will give you a some time to eat and socialize with other attendees.
 \n \nIf you can\, please sign up to bring something for the cookout: https:
 //goo.gl/mJTk9e\n \nEveryone should have everything setup and in place by 6
 :45pm. I will explain how the CTF works and make sure everyone can connect 
 to the scoreboard. I will start transmitting flags at 7pm.\n \nThe goal of 
 this is to come out and have some SDR fun!
LAST-MODIFIED:20171216T232911Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Court #105\, Severn\, MD\, United Sta
 tes
