DESCRIPTION:<br>https://www.meetup.com/Unallocated-Space/events/246732370/<
 br><br>Come join a new challenging project at the Unallocated Space\, RSC M
 akerspace\, or HacDC.<br><br>This is a high-altitude balloon employing scie
 ntific monitoring devices as it ascends to heights of 100\,000+ ft. (see th
 is wiki (<a title="https://wiki.hacdc.org/index.php/HacDC_Spaceblimp" class
 ="link" href="https://wiki.hacdc.org/index.php/HacDC_Spaceblimp" target="__
 blank"><font color="#0066cc">https://wiki.hacdc.org/index.php/HacDC_Spacebl
 imp</font></a>) for past efforts and info)<br><br>Our group will create a d
 evice package and plan for the variety of difficult issues that occur at hi
 gh altitude. If you have interest in atmospheric\, environmental\, and/or s
 pace science\, radio telemetry\, or just interested in great projects - ple
 ase join us bi-weekly on Wednesdays 6:30pm.<br><br>This is joint project wi
 th members of Unallocated Space\, Rockville Science Center\, and HacDC.\n\n
 Join with Google Hangouts: https://plus.google.com/hangouts/_/calendar/dW5h
 bGxvY2F0ZWRzcGFjZWhxQGdtYWlsLmNvbQ.1m1v9ej92sbsl9iruabj88l9lj?hs=121
LAST-MODIFIED:20180117T232243Z
