DESCRIPTION:\nJoin us at Unallocated Space for our monthly Crafternoon even
 t! This month's topic will be: Macrame or Decorative Knot Tying\n\nDATE: 15
 SEPT2018\n\nTIME: 1200-1500\n\nTOPIC: Macrame or Decorative Knot Tying\n\nS
 UMMARY:  We'll be learning how to make decorative wall hangings using macra
 me.\n\nGOAL: To learn 5 basic macrame knots in order to make a decorative w
 all hanging.\n\n  -  Larks Head Knot\n  -  Square Knot\n  -  Half Square Kn
 ot\n  -  Double Hitch\n  -  Half Hitch\n\nSUPPLIES YOU'LL NEED TO BRING: \n
 \n\n200ft chord of either 3-5 mm synthetic or cotton. This depends on (more
  or less) the size of your project. You may can find supplies at your local
  hobby store\, such as Joann fabric\, Hobby Lobby\, or Amazon.\n\nhttps://w
 ww.amazon.com/Stillness-Crafts-3mm-Macrame-Cord/dp/B073R25MT4\n\nSingle dow
 el rod\, stick\, or metal hoop the size depends on personal preference. \nh
 ttps://www.amazon.com/Benvo-Catcher-Dreamcatchers-Projects-Different/dp/B07
 DHP15PG\n\n\nOPTIONAL SUPPLIES:\n\nSynthetic flowers\, greenery\, or accent
  items to incorporate.\nWooden beads that are made for macrame . These are 
 not normal beads and have very large holes through the center.\nFeathers\n\
 nEXAMPLES: \nhttps://www.facebook.com/events/1085219611638004/permalink/108
 5219998304632/\n\nSKILL LEVEL: Everyone\n\nPRESENTER: Whitney
LAST-MODIFIED:20180912T005903Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Crafternoon: Macrame or Decorative Knot Tying
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
