BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20171026T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20171026T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20171026T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:SPL101 – Splunk more than just cool T-shirts\nDATE: 26OCT2017\n
 TIME: 1900-2100\nTOPIC: INFOSEC NIGHT: Intro to Splunk\n\nSUMMARY:  \nWe ar
 e going to an introduction to Splunk. Topics that we will go over will incl
 ude parts of the Splunk architecture. How to integrate Splunk with other te
 chnologies. Using Splunk as a SIEM. How to get free Splunk licenses and fre
 e official training.    \nGOAL: Understand the basics of Splunk\, Install/C
 onfigure Splunk and run basic SPL queries. \nThings to bring: Laptop (optio
 nal) and questions about Splunk   \n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone\nPRESENTER: JR
 \n\nhttps://www.meetup.com/Unallocated-Space/events/244387417/
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Intro to Splunk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20171109T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20171109T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20171109T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:DATE: 09NOV2017\nTOPIC: INFOSEC NIGHT: Cryptographic Components
  of TLS/SSL\nSUMMARY: We will cover the basics of how TLS/SSL works to secu
 re HTTP traffic. Topics will cover Symmetric cryptography\, Asymmetric cryp
 tography\, Keyed hashing\, and Key establishment.\nGOAL: Understand how the
  components of TLS/SSL work together to provide secure communication across
  the world wide web.\nSKILL LEVEL: Everyone\nPRESENTER: BobbyR
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Cryptographic Components of TLS/SSL
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20171207T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20171207T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20171207T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:<div dir="auto">TOPIC: INFOSEC NIGHT: Splunk&nbsp\;<div dir="au
 to">SUMMARY:&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<div dir="auto">First we go over any Splunk quest
 ions and do a review of the SPL101 course. Next we are going to go deeper i
 nto various Splunk functions. Then unleash the power of Splunk with Regular
  Expression. Finally tips and tricks for our Splunk CTF.&nbsp\;<div dir="au
 to">GOAL: Learn a little more about Splunk and how to create new fields wit
 h Regular Expression and filter unwanted data to keep license cost low.&nbs
 p\; &nbsp\;<div dir="auto">WHAT TO BRING: Laptop with Splunk and Developer 
 license.&nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;<div dir="auto">SKILL LEVEL:&nbsp\; Everyone&
 nbsp\;<div dir="auto">PRESENTER: JR
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: SPL102 – Splunk  >= e|i|f|grep|Select-String        
                                                         
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
