BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20180315T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20180315T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180315T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: We will cover the basics of the Tor anonymity network 
 including operation\, use cases\, strengths\, weaknesses\, and what onions 
 have to do with it.\n\nGOAL: Understand what Tor is\, how it works\, and ho
 w it can be a useful tool in your privacy toolbox.\n\nSKILL LEVEL: Everyone
 \n\nPRESENTER: BobbyR
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Tor Explained
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20180329T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20180329T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180329T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY:  \nTonight we are going to talk about the basics of ma
 lware analysis\, and we are going to do it by live detonating a few malicio
 us files on screen and going through the findings together. This will be on
 e part Q & A and one part live fire exercise as we talk about some of the b
 asics of malware analysis such as determining callouts\, finding malicious 
 processes\, and looking at registry changes. We will also talk about some o
 f the basics of building a malware sandbox yourself and what tools you migh
 t want to try to get started. This will be manual dynamic analysis\, so no 
 sandboxing unless there is some time to go over sandbox reporting.\n\nGOAL:
  \nDetonate some malware and see what it does\n\nTHINGS TO BRING:  \nQuesti
 ons and comments\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  \nEveryone\n\nPRESENTER: \nUnderstudy
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Intro to Malware Analysis
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20180412T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20180412T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180412T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:You got the overview in intro to Malware Analysis\, now lets pu
 t it to the test and get behind the keyboard. Bring a spare computer becaus
 e tonight you are going to build your very own malware analysis environment
 . We will be focusing on the things we covered before\, such as installing 
 Remnux and getting a VM up with some good tools\, we may even do Cuckoo san
 dbox if there is time. After that we can put it to the test\, I’ll have a f
 ew malicious files on hand that you can run and analyze on the lab you just
  built. Lets move past the theory and get you started on the work. Don’t wo
 rry if you missed the first class\, I’m happy to cover the topics again as 
 we build out these machines.<br><br>GOAL: Build a malware analysis lab mach
 ine<br><br>Things to bring:&nbsp\; <br><br>REQUIRED:<br><br>A laptop or com
 puter you can install Linux on\, bonus points if you can pre install Ubuntu
  14.04 before class (Must be 14.04 on a 64 bit computer)<br><br>A flash dri
 ve(s) for the transfer of information<br><br>SUGGESTED:<br><br>A copy of Wi
 ndows\, Windows 7 is preferred but any copy you have will do <u>NOTE: we ca
 n set these up with developer copies of Windows which will work fine if you
  don’t have access to Windows yourself.<br></u><br>Copy of Microsoft Office
 <br><br>SKILL LEVEL:&nbsp\; Everyone<br><br>PRESENTER: Understudy
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
