DESCRIPTION:A high-level introduction to Red Teaming. Often times\, Red Tea
 ming is confused with penetration testing. This overview will go over diffe
 rences between the two\, special considerations when performing Red Team op
 erations\, and will attempt to the connect the "what now?" of penetration t
 esting with Red Teaming.\n\nGOAL: Introduce Red Teaming operations and conc
 epts\n\nThings to bring: (SUGGESTED) Note taking materials. This will be a 
 largely theoretical presentation to introduce concepts that will be leverag
 ed during more hands-on presentations later.\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone. Bas
 ic knowledge of penetration testing methodology would help but will be cove
 red during the talk.\n\nPRESENTER: nyte
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Introduction to Red Teaming
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20180509T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20180509T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180510T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, May 9 is a Metasploit-themed InfoSec night! Based o
 n your votes\, we'll have a hands-on Metasploit introduction session from 6
 :30-8:30\, pizza dinner from 8:30-9:00\, then a Mettle universal payload de
 monstration at 9:00. Seating will be limited\, so arrive on-time! (No promi
 ses\, but we'll do our best to record and livestream via Google Hangouts!) 
 Bring $5 cash for pizza and your laptop to join in the hands-on session.\n\
 nAt 6:30\, we'll start with a brief explanation of what Metasploit is\, how
  the framework is architected\, and how to download and install Metasploit.
  Then we'll take a look at how to use msfconsole\, create payloads with msf
 venom\, find exploits\, use them\, and gain remote code execution on a targ
 et. Finally\, we'll tour Meterpreter to learn about how we can investigate 
 a compromised workstation\, establish persistence\, and gain further access
  into the network.\n\nAt 9:00\, we'll switch gears to demonstrate the Mettl
 e universal payload\, along with some recent updates that allow us to use t
 he payload to launch further exploits into the network. We'll talk about ex
 ploiting a router to call back to our attacker workstation\, then leveragin
 g that access to get further into the network. We'll end the night with Met
 tle running on a home-office router\, then let folks play around and ask qu
 estions!\n\nTo participate in the hands-on portion\, you'll need: a laptop 
 with VMware Workstation/Fusion/VirtualBox\, an extra 4GB of RAM to run two/
 three VMs and\, for those of you on Macbooks\, the ability to connect to a 
 USB thumbdrive and wired Ethernet network.
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Metasploit
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
