BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20180607T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20180607T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180607T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a new job is tough. Finding talent for open jobs is
  tough. The recruitment and interview process is hard enough as it is\; let
 's not make it more difficult than it has to be. Let's pull back the curtai
 n a bit\, leave our egos at the door and talk about some real (maybe extrem
 e) examples of #recruiterfail and #candidatefail in an attempt to break dow
 n the barriers between recruiters and applicants in a fun and comfortable w
 ay.\n\nGoal: Share a few tips on how to deal with recruiters\, but also pro
 vide some considerations for how to present and sell yourself (online\, cor
 respondence\, and in-person) during the process.\n\nThings to bring: Questi
 ons\, comments\, sense of humor\, and a resume if we have time to review it
 .\n\nSkill level: Everyone\nPresenter: Brian Sheridan & Matt Duren\, Tenabl
 e Recruiting Team
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: #recruiterfail vs #candidatefail
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
