DESCRIPTION:CRYPTO101 - What puts the S in HTTPS?\n\n\nSUMMARY: We will cov
 er the basics of how TLS/SSL works to secure HTTP traffic. Topics will cove
 r Symmetric cryptography\, Asymmetric cryptography\, Keyed hashing\, and Ke
 y establishment.\n\nGOAL: Understand how the components of TLS/SSL work tog
 ether to provide secure communication across the world wide web.\n\nSKILL L
 EVEL: Everyone\nPRESENTER: Bobby R
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Cryptographic Components of TLS/SSL
TRANSP:OPAQUE
