UID:mlgalfovor1a1pb2rdvamseabk@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180719T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:In this session\, we will review the basics of how network traf
 fic flows\, with a discussion of the OSI model and TCP/IP stack\, and explo
 re the various features of Wireshark\, which is a network protocol analyzer
 .  We will use custom-built packet captures to explore network protocols an
 d malicious network activity.  \n\nGOAL: Gain a working knowledge of networ
 k traffic analysis using Wireshark.  \n\nTHINGS TO BRING:  Laptop with Wire
 shark installed for your OS\n\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone\nPRESENTER: Marcell
 e\, Women’s Society of Cyberjutsu
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Packet Analysis with Wireshark
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
