RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180802T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:DESCRIPTION: Understanding binary conversion and how networks a
 re broken up is a foundational skill to networking\, troubleshooting\, pack
 et analysis\, and much more. In this session we will review basic IPv4 subn
 etting\, beginning with an explanation of number systems\, binary\, and cla
 ssful IP addressing\, and continue into discussing Classless-Inter Domain R
 outing (CIDR)\, subnetting\, supernetting\, and variable length subnetting.
 \n\nThis class is the first part of a 2 part series that will continue into
  discussing how to use this information for offensive security (presented b
 y Gomi).\n\n01000101 01100001 01110011 01111001\n\nGOAL: Gain or strengthen
  your knowledge of subnetting.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: pen and paper\n\nSKILL L
 EVEL: Everyone\n\nPRESENTER: Rizbek
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Subnetting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
