RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20180816T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Tonight we will go over how common network diagnostic tools wor
 k\, and how we can use them to reverse engineer network topologies to deter
 mine subnets\, routers\, and firewalls. Then we'll explain how to do this s
 impler\, with less noise\, using a modified tool.\n\n\nGOAL: Map out target
  networks and discover routes\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone who took the Subnet
 ting class\nPRESENTER: Gomi
LAST-MODIFIED:20181105T172403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Offensive Subnetting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
