CREATED:20180713T014515Z
DESCRIPTION:Course Description: ​This progressive\, hands-on course will co
 ver the fundamentals<br>of electronics\, including direct current (DC)\, al
 ternating current (AC)\, and<br>semiconductors. As we progress though the c
 ourse we'll build and analyze a variable DC power supply\, then build an au
 dio amplifier.<br><br>Instructor: Corey Koval (corey@unallocatedspace.org)<
 br><br>Required Materials:<br><ul><li>Notebook<br></li><li>Pen/Pencils<br><
 /li><li>Scientific Calculator<br></li><li>Variable DC power supply: https:/
 /www.jameco.com/z/JE215-Dual-Output-Adjustable-Linear-Regulated-Power-Suppl
 y-Kit_20626.html (DO NOT ASSEMBLE!)<br></li><li>Resistor assortment http://
 www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/RS125/RS125-ND/7108<br></li><li>Digital M
 ultimeter: http://www.circuitspecialists.com/digital-multimeter-csi2010.htm
 l<br></li><li>Breadboard http://www.circuitspecialists.com/wb-102+j.html<br
 ></li><li>jumper wires (with and without alligator clips) https://www.circu
 itspecialists.com/m000f0002.html<br></li><li>Magnifying glass if you need o
 ne to see up close<br></li></ul><br><br><br>Course Outline<br>Topic #1: DC:
  ​definitions\, voltage\, current\, electrons\, how electrons flow\, Ohm’s<
 br>law\, resistors\, resistor color code\, resistor dividers\, series circu
 its\, parallel<br>circuits\, series-parallel circuits\, power\, diodes\, sw
 itches and circuit protection\,<br>capacitors\, inductors<br>Topic #2: AC: 
 ​frequency\, waveforms\, capacitors\, capacitive reactance\,<br>inductors\,
  inductive reactance\, impedance\, RLC circuits\, transformers\, rectifiers
 \,<br>voltage regulators<br>Topic #3: Semiconductors: ​transistors\, amplif
 iers
LAST-MODIFIED:20181110T010705Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Electronics Fundamentals I: DC Circuits
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
