DESCRIPTION:\nSUMMARY:  This will be the final presentation in my Red Team 
 series. We will briefly review material covered in Red Team 201\, then roll
  right into Linux and Windows Exploitation\, Tunneling/Port Forwarding\, Wi
 ndows Enumeration\, Credential Stealing/Reuse\, Active Directory Enumeratio
 n\, and Domain Hopping.\n\nGOAL: Provide attendees with intermediate unders
 tanding of exploitation techniques.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Computer with Kali 
 Linux natively installed or running as a VM. Be able to connect wirelessly 
 to a closed network. Note taking materials.\n\nLEVEL:  Individuals with bas
 ic understanding of networking concepts. Topics will be explained as they a
 re covered.\nPRESENTER: nyte
LAST-MODIFIED:20181127T151403Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Red Teaming 202
TRANSP:OPAQUE
