UID:01m92nfigrov5is8cvft3vvlju@google.com
CREATED:20190106T015812Z
DESCRIPTION:\nOriginally called Textile’s Sewer (since soiree is hard to pr
 onounce and spell)\, this event is dedicated to sharing information about a
 nything technical or just awesome. As Technology Enthusiasts\, most of us a
 re constantly learning about new technologies. \n\n\nThe Minicon is a event
  dedicated to sharing what we have learned with others. Speakers can use th
 is as a way to practice their talks before conferences and/or just practice
  their speaking skills and get feedback. \n\n\nIf you have a request for a 
 topic or are interested in giving a talk\, contact Pronto via the google gr
 oup\, meetup group\, in person or whatever other medium you prefer. If any 
 presenters want to share their presentation\, please make a request via our
  Github.\n\nThis January 12th we have:\n\nPut Yourself in Someone Else's Sh
 oes: Taking a Look At Security From The Mind of a Hacker by Kevin Figueroa\
 nWant to stop your organization from being hacked? What are the first steps
  you need to take when developing strategic plans to keep your organization
  safe? In order to create successful plans and strategies\, many different 
 components are needed\, which will help you from being breached. One elemen
 t needed is to take a look at your networks from the mind of a malicious at
 tacker. Listen in to start thinking about how malicious attackers can misus
 e web application and take advantage of vulnerabilities through exploitatio
 n techniques in order to compromise and breach network infrastructures. We 
 will analyze the following:\nThe type of malicious threat actors and attack
  types\nAssessing the current attacker behavior\nWhat information are they 
 really after\n\n"how to fu** everything" talk on fuzzing and symbolic execu
 tion\nPractical Exploitation with fuzzing & symbolic execution\n\nPresented
  by Lojikil\n\nHexia @hexadecim8  Emily Crose\nmalware campaign\n\nRaymond 
 Gabler\nCTF/Pentesting workflows and tools to help manage them - talk will 
 start from the generic sense and build into a toolset that helps in this re
 alm.\nhttps://pentest.ws/\npentest.ws\nPenetration Testing Workshop - PenTe
 st.WS\nEasily track hosts\, services and vulnerabilities during a CTF or pe
 ntest lab.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190112T031038Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Minicon
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
