RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;COUNT=8;INTERVAL=1;BYDAY=TU
EXDATE;TZID=America/New_York:20190528T190000
EXDATE;TZID=America/New_York:20190625T190000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:7vdur9sn8f2fpmpt4ga2tmk0ip@google.com
CREATED:20190503T003546Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: Do you like solving ciphers but want to grow beyond ro
 t13 puzzles? Are you interested in steamy romances involving Alice\, Bob\, 
 and Eve? Do you want to learn how to crack one time pads? Do you want to kn
 ow how you're using SSL wrong? Or maybe you're doing SSL right\, but you ke
 ep hearing about this BEAST attack and want to understand it on a cryptolog
 ist's level? Did you ever want to take the Stanford Online Crypto Course bu
 t feared the math?\n\nThen the Stanford Crypto 1 Study Group is the event o
 f the year for you! Together we will conquer the math and mystery of Crypto
 . Break down nerdy concepts into everyday concepts.\n\nThe Stanford Crypto 
 1 course is an online course provided by Coursera. The course begins with a
  detailed discussion of how two parties who have\na shared secret key can c
 ommunicate securely when a powerful adversary\neavesdrops and tampers with 
 traffic. The second half of\nthe course discusses public-key techniques tha
 t let two parties generate\na shared secret key. Throughout the course part
 icipants will be exposed\nto many exciting open problems in the field and w
 ork on fun\nprogramming projects.\n\nhttps://www.coursera.org/learn/crypto\
 n\nThe study sessions is for people to point out areas of the material that
  they didnt understand\, and for everyone else to come up with the best way
  to explain it. PLEASE DO NOT BE AFRAID TO SAY YOU DON'T KNOW SOMETHING. Th
 is is crypto\, we know its difficult\, that's why we find it alluring. Toge
 ther we'll be able to help each other. No judging\, No shame. #ELI5\n\nPyth
 on is language of choice\, but we'll try to accommodate others as best as p
 ossible\n\nTL\;DR: If you take this class\, you will be able to complete CT
 F Crypto challenges!\n\nGOAL: Complete the Stanford Crypto Course 1 like a 
 boss\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Your development environment of choice\, and somet
 hing to take notes in\n\nSKILL LEVEL: Algebra is nice\, Calculus is great\,
  but not mandatory. Functional programming is highly suggested.\n\nPRESENTE
 R: VirusFriendly
LAST-MODIFIED:20190503T040518Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Severn\, MD
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Stanford Crypto 1 Study Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20190530T220000Z
DTEND:20190531T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0kt15jhfrddnqtgheappkkpocq@google.com
CREATED:20190506T225043Z
DESCRIPTION:CACI Cyber Tech Talk: Introduction to Binary Reverse Engineerin
 g\n\nWill Klinger (Offensive Security Exploitation Expert – OSEE) will disc
 uss how to get started in software reverse engineering using static analysi
 s tools such as IDApro\, Ghidra\, etc.\n\nCACI will provide food and refres
 hments.  If you have interest in working for CACI\, talent acquisition will
  also be available.\n\n\n\nEvent will be from 6pm to 9pm and the talk will 
 start at 7pm.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190506T225043Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CACI Cyber Tech Talk: Introduction to Binary Reverse Engineering
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20190525T160000Z
DTEND:20190526T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:65i3gp1l6cr6cb9n75h32b9k6ss3eb9pc5hj8bb369hjap1ic9i38p36cg@google.com
CREATED:20190425T165939Z
DESCRIPTION:Yes\, we're bringing you another epic twelve hours of gaming an
 d fragging fun!!\n\nBring a dish or snacks to share\, if you wish\, and we'
 ll have a spread for lunch and snacking! We'll likely order pizza around th
 e dinner hour\, so bring $5-10 to get in on that action.\n\nBring your gami
 ng rig\, whether laptop or desktop\, your **UPDATED** games/clients/OS\, po
 tluck item(s)\, and an appetite for destruction and mayhem (virtual\, that 
 is.)\n\n\nTentative Schedule:\n--------------------------------------------
 --------------------------------\n12pm - 3pm Setup\n3pm - 5pm Free Play (we
 'll see what people are interested in)\n5pm - 6pm Minecraft Hunger Games St
 yle Deathmatch\n6pm FOOD!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
 !!!!!!!!!!\n6pm- 12am Free Play (we'll see what people are interested in)\n
 \n\nGames We Typically Play or Have Seen Interest In:\n--------------------
 --------------------------------------------------------\n- Minecraft PvP -
  Hunger Games style ~ Team Deathmatch [You need a MC Account to play]\n- L4
 D2 - (4 player Co-op or 8 player 4v4 versus)\n- TF2 - (TF2. You know what i
 t is.) [FREE]\n- Evolve - (4v1 class game\; monster vs hunters) [FREE]\n- K
 illing Floor / Killing Floor 2\n- Overwatch\n- Quake 2 / 3 - (Retro FPS Dea
 thmatch)\n- UT2K4 - (Team Deathmatch FPS)\n- Brawlhalla - (Similar to smash
  bros.\, but cross-platform) [FREE]\n- Doom / Doom 2 [FREE]\n- Guns of Icar
 us Online - (Team-controlled Steampunk Airship Deathmatch)\n- Move or Die -
  (Multiplayer\, 4 Player Versus)\n- Rocket League - (Racing + Soccer)\n- De
 ad Realm - (Multiplayer Horror)\n- Descent - (Retro Team Deathmatch OR Co-o
 p\, Vertigo) [FREE]\n\nPlease let us know if you have any additional game s
 uggestions\, questions\, or comments.\n\nWe're really excited for this even
 t and expect it to be an EPIC evening of fun and surprises!!\n\nWhile all e
 vents at Unallocated Space are free to all\, we do ask that you consider ma
 king a donation to help us keep putting on events like this and others. You
 r support is what keeps the lights on!!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190508T032946Z
LOCATION:512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Epic LAN Party
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
