 sts\, and Wireless CTFers who want to improve their understanding of the fu
 ndamentals of digital signal processing and other RF or basic Electrical En
 gineering concepts by using existing tools\, techniques\, and hardware to w
 ork on practical problems\n\nGOAL:\nImprove signal processing fundamentals 
 through practical applications using basic SDR tools and techniques\n\nTHIN
 GS TO BRING:\nLaptop with your preferred SDR software (Recommendation for b
 eginners: Ubuntu or Pentoo running on your machine or a bootable flash driv
 e --not in a VM)\n(Optional) SDR hardware (Recommendation for beginners: RT
 L-SDR)\n\nSKILL LEVEL:\nAny skill level is fine\, experts should expect to 
 have some questions pointed their way\n\nPRESENTER:\nSteve or Corey or anyo
 ne else who has a topic they want to discuss
