CREATED:20190624T235630Z
DESCRIPTION:DATE: 27July2019\n\nTIME: 0900-1800 (with a break for lunch)\n\
 nTOPIC: Red Team Boot Camp\n\nSUMMARY:\n\n\nHave you ever had the opportuni
 ty to run a Red Team engagement in a corporate environment? Or maybe you've
  taken some ethical hacking courses but struggle with the "now what?" aspec
 t of offensive security? Well now's your chance to expand on your skill set
 ! This boot camp offers attendees the opportunity to operate in a Windows D
 omain environment. Attendees will learn about computer network exploitation
  tradecraft\, red team tactics\, and what differentiates a Red Team engagem
 ent from your standard Penetration Test. Penetration Testing methodology wi
 ll be covered\, however the boot camp will focus heavily on post-exploitati
 on tactics used in modern\, real-world Red Team engagements.\n\n\nTopics co
 vered include introduction to Penetration Testing and Red Teaming\, Introdu
 ction to Metasploit\, Introduction to basic Windows/Linux commands\, Introd
 uction to Tunneling\, Open-source enumeration\, Target enumeration\, Linux/
 Windows Exploitation\, Persistence Methods\, Local vs Domain Accounts\, Act
 ive Directory Enumeration\, and Pivoting through Multiple Domains.\n\n\nGOA
 L: Provide an intro to advanced level of training in Red Team tactics and t
 echniques\n\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: A fully patched Kali Linux distribution\, e
 ither on bare metal or as a VM. If in a VM\, ensure your distro can connect
  to a network in "Bridged Mode". Note taking materials are also highly reco
 mmended.\n\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Basic knowledge of networking and security prin
 ciples are highly encouraged.\n\n\nPRESENTER: nyte\n\n\nNote: Seats may be 
 limited and are first come\, first served. While our events are always free
 \, donations are always appreciated \;)
LAST-MODIFIED:20190624T235654Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Red Team Boot Camp
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190702T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190702T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:7vdur9sn8f2fpmpt4ga2tmk0ip@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190702T190000
CREATED:20190503T003546Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: Do you like solving ciphers but want to grow beyond ro
 t13 puzzles? Are you interested in steamy romances involving Alice\, Bob\, 
 and Eve? Do you want to learn how to crack one time pads? Do you want to kn
 ow how you're using SSL wrong? Or maybe you're doing SSL right\, but you ke
 ep hearing about this BEAST attack and want to understand it on a cryptolog
 ist's level? Did you ever want to take the Stanford Online Crypto Course bu
 t feared the math?\n\nThen the Stanford Crypto 1 Study Group is the event o
 f the year for you! Together we will conquer the math and mystery of Crypto
 . Break down nerdy concepts into everyday concepts.\n\nThe Stanford Crypto 
 1 course is an online course provided by Coursera. The course begins with a
  detailed discussion of how two parties who have\na shared secret key can c
 ommunicate securely when a powerful adversary\neavesdrops and tampers with 
 traffic. The second half of\nthe course discusses public-key techniques tha
 t let two parties generate\na shared secret key. Throughout the course part
 icipants will be exposed\nto many exciting open problems in the field and w
 ork on fun\nprogramming projects.\n\nhttps://www.coursera.org/learn/crypto\
 n\nThe study sessions is for people to point out areas of the material that
  they didnt understand\, and for everyone else to come up with the best way
  to explain it. PLEASE DO NOT BE AFRAID TO SAY YOU DON'T KNOW SOMETHING. Th
 is is crypto\, we know its difficult\, that's why we find it alluring. Toge
 ther we'll be able to help each other. No judging\, No shame. #ELI5\n\nPyth
 on is language of choice\, but we'll try to accommodate others as best as p
 ossible\n\nTL\;DR: If you take this class\, you will be able to complete CT
 F Crypto challenges!\n\nGOAL: Complete the Stanford Crypto Course 1 like a 
 boss\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Your development environment of choice\, and somet
 hing to take notes in\n\nSKILL LEVEL: Algebra is nice\, Calculus is great\,
  but not mandatory. Functional programming is highly suggested.\n\nPRESENTE
 R: VirusFriendly
LAST-MODIFIED:20190702T025757Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, Severn\, MD
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CANCELLED: Stanford Crypto 1 Study Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20190719T230000Z
DTEND:20190720T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0aubm9ap30543cbceuqohvjqmt@google.com
CREATED:20190703T001539Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: \n\n3D Digital art and computer graphics are used for 
 creating animated films\, visual effects\, 3D printing\, interactive 3D app
 lications\, and video games. Everything from Toy Story The Movie to Apple\,
  the computer company heavily utilize 3D digital art. \n\nThe class will st
 art with conveying the value of modeling and animation by showing the profe
 ssional\, technical\, and artistic opportunities for someone who understand
 s 3D modeling and animation.  During the class students will learn how to u
 se free software to create 3D digital Art and animation.  The course will e
 nable students to begin to create and animate from their imagination.  \n\n
 The topics in the course will be:\n\nLearning the Software interface\n\nCre
 ating geometric objects like cubes and cylinders\n\nMoving objects in 3 dim
 ensions\n\nCreating new shapes from existing objects\n\nMaterials and color
 s\n\nVirtual Camera control\n\nCreating print and video worthy scenes and a
 nimations\n\n\nGOAL:\n\nBy the end of the course\, students will be capable
  of doing a simple model and animation of their own.\n\n\nTHINGS TO BRING:\
 n\n Equipment needs for the course are just a computer and a 3 button (two 
 buttons with a mouse wheel) mouse. The software needed is Blender 3D\, whic
 h is completely free.  Blender runs on Windows\, Mac\, and Linux\, so as lo
 ng as you have a full operating system\, it should work fine.\n\n\nSKILL LE
 VEL:  \n\nBASIC \n\n\nPRESENTER:  \n\nWILLIAM HARRISON
LAST-MODIFIED:20190703T001606Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:3D Digital Art and Animation Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
