BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20190911T220000Z
DTEND:20190912T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2h5ccl0vcdhro542b9ui7puhig@google.com
CREATED:20190909T154434Z
DESCRIPTION:\nInstructor: Surefire\n\nWhat if you could use a Rasperry Pi t
 o protect your network from nation-state grade attacks?  What if you could 
 definitively confirm that you've never been hacked by BlueKeep\, even befor
 e anyone knew about it?\n\nZeek (formerly BroIDS) is an open-source network
  monitoring tool.  Unlike Snort\, Surricata\, and other IDSes\, Zeek doesn'
 t use signatures.  Instead\, it inspects dozens of protocols and saves just
  enough metadata to let you look back in time.  Using this data\, you can s
 ee if you've been affected by vulnerabilities even before they became publi
 c.\n\nWe'll spend an evening talking about how to setup Zeek in a Debian pl
 atform (like an Ubuntu VM or a Raspberry Pi).  From there\, we'll learn how
  to interpret output logs to learn more about the traffic on your network.\
 n\nProposed schedule:\n   6pm - We'll be ready to help folks get a RasPi/Ub
 untu VM setup for the evening\n   7pm - Lecure to introduce Zeek and show h
 ow to get it set up\n   8pm - Demonstrate monitoring traffic and replaying 
 PCAPs to catch BlueKeep scans\n   9pm - Wrap up for the evening
LAST-MODIFIED:20190910T023225Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Intro to Zeek: How a RasPi can keep you safe from BlueKeep
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
