UID:6dje1k5bdeo144q27b9sc04o2m@google.com
CREATED:20190916T001348Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY:The prop making workshop is intended to teach the skill
 s necessary for making anime and stage props. We well be covering Resin cas
 ting\, 3D modeling\, 3D printing and hand crafting realistic props. Our Gue
 st Aaron Gronowski is a professional modeler and Maya instructor. His sough
 t after Link swords and shields can be viewed at  <a href="http://www.fiber
 glassblades.com/Blades.html">http://www.fiberglassblades.com/Blades.html</a
 > and <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/FiberglassBlades">https://www.etsy
 .com/shop/FiberglassBlades</a>. James and Bowie will be covering hand craft
 ing and molding techniques. Bring Clip art and sketches of the objects you 
 want to make or half finished projects and we will show you how to complete
  them. Or Just Bring yourself and take notes.<br><br>GOAL:<br>To demonstrat
 e 3D Modeling\, 3D printing\, Hand crafting and Molding Props<br><br>THINGS
  TO BRING:Sketches and Clip art of your prop (as many views as you can find
 . Top/Side/bottom)\, Soft measuring tape\, note Book and/or laptop.<br><br>
 If you want to work with Foam Bring Extruded polyurethane Foam insulation\,
  Epoxy filler\, Polyurethane resin (for closed foam) \, Electric sander\, S
 andpaper.<br><br>If you want to work with Molds bring Resin\, mold rubber o
 r silicon\, Brown Hardboard Wall Panel\, hot glue gun.<br><br>Supply links<
 br><br><a href="https://www.smooth-on.com/">https://www.smooth-on.com/</a><
 br><br><a href="https://www.homedepot.com/">https://www.homedepot.com/</a><
 br><br><a href="https://www.micromark.com/">https://www.micromark.com/</a><
 br><br>Do not Go Crazy. This can be done on the cheap. You do not need gall
 ons of resin or Hundreds of dollars. Use some sense if unsure\, just come t
 o the workshop and we will show you how.<br><br>SKILL LEVEL:0 to advanced<b
 r><br>PRESENTER:James Hall\, Bowie Hall and Aaron Gronowski
LAST-MODIFIED:20190923T104724Z
LOCATION:512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Prop Making Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
