CREATED:20191014T200449Z
DESCRIPTION:\nCACI presents Domain Specific Model-based Systems Engineering
  (DS-MBSE)\, a key capability that enables systems engineers and software d
 evelopers to pictorially model software-centric systems on a drawing canvas
  which transforms the models into machine- and human-readable code\, script
 s\, data\, and configuration files. Using DevOps and other channels\, these
  generated artifacts can then be rapidly deployed to automate system operat
 ion and adaptation per dynamic mission requirements. Moreover\, our models 
 can be reasoned over by machine to provide automated decision support and d
 esign space analysis. The main conceptual use cases for DS-MBSE include mod
 eling and simulation platform orchestration (e.g. cyber ranges)\, artificia
 l intelligence (AI) toolchain composition\, AI assurance and security imple
 mentation\, cyber defense course of action (COA) analysis\, communication s
 ystem architecture adaptation\, and real-time battlefield asset integration
 .  We are currently using Vanderbilt University’s open source Web Generic M
 odeling Environment (webgme.org) to create domain specific languages\, mode
 l compilers\, and code generators. With DS-MBSE\, we can begin to design an
 d build truly adaptive software-centric systems that respond to changes at 
 different time scales.
LAST-MODIFIED:20191029T013156Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rapid System Automation via Domain Specific Modeling
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
