UID:5ktc7ep9ar7jqu584p1erj1ehd@google.com
CREATED:20191217T142718Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>COMBATTING CYBER PROPAGANDA &amp\; DISINFORMATION IN
  A DIGITALLY ILLITERATE WORLD - Workshop Day 1</strong></p><p><strong>SUMMA
 RY:&nbsp\;</strong>This course is an active participation course that will 
 engage participants and give them the tools they need to understand\, asses
 s\, and take action related to cyber deception campaigns (CDCs). The course
  will introduce participants to the theory of CDCs\, historical instances o
 f CDCs\, and how CDCs are conducted. This course will be taught over two da
 ys\, and separated into 4 modules: Information Operations Theory\, Analysis
  of Historical CDCs\, Modern Tactics Techniques and Procedures (TTPs)\, and
  Becoming the Operator.</p><p>Participants who pass this course will be giv
 en a certificate of completion demonstrating basic knowledge of online prop
 aganda operations.</p><p></p><br><b>Bio:&nbsp\;</b>Chris Sampson is the Chi
 ef of Research for the Terror Asymmetrics Project on Strategies\, Tactics a
 nd Radical Ideology (TAPSTRI). He has been conducting various operations to
  infiltrate extremist groups on the internet since 2009 including ISIS\, AQ
 \, white supremacists and other organizations. Beyond his day to day\, he i
 s most notably the New York Times Bestselling Author of&nbsp\;<i>Hacking IS
 IS</i>&nbsp\;- a book coauthored by Malcom Nance on the efforts to track\, 
 infiltrate and destroy ISIS online propaganda environment. Chris also acted
  as the lead researcher for&nbsp\;<i>Defeating ISIS\, Plot To Hack America\
 , Plot To Destroy Democracy&nbsp\;</i>and&nbsp\;<i>Plot To Betray Democracy
 </i>\, and as the researcher for 2<sup>nd</sup>&nbsp\;edition of&nbsp\;<i>T
 he Terrorists of Iraq</i>. His twenty five years in media development for o
 nline marketing\, development\, server administration and infosec combined 
 with his ten years in radio and television production for Pacifica radio\, 
 Free Speech TV\, and other related organizations has equipped Chris with th
 e polished skill set and specialized training in the art\, culture\, langua
 ge and politics of India\, Middle East and North Africa and South Africa.<p
 ><strong><br>THINGS TO BRING:&nbsp\;</strong>Laptop\, pen\, &amp\; paper</p
 ><p></p><p><strong>AUDIENCE:&nbsp\;</strong></p><p>Academia: Understand Onl
 ine Propaganda</p><ul><li>Sociology</li><li>Technology</li><li>Communicatio
 ns</li></ul><p>Law Enforcement: How Influence Works</p><ul><li>Intelligence
 </li></ul><p>Private Sector: How Are Ideas Spreading</p><ul><li>Threat Inte
 lligence</li><li>Marketing</li></ul><p><strong>AUDIENCE:<br></strong></p><u
 l><li>Academia: Understand Online Propaganda</li></ul><ul><li>Sociology</li
 ><li>Technology</li><li>Communications</li></ul><ul><li>Law Enforcement: Ho
 w Influence Works</li></ul><ul><li>Intelligence</li></ul><ul><li>Private Se
 ctor: How Are Ideas Spreading</li></ul><ul><li>Threat Intelligence</li><li>
 Marketing</li></ul><p>Keyholder: Jelly</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200113T134932Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:COMBATTING CYBER PROPAGANDA & DISINFORMATION IN A DIGITALLY ILLITER
 ATE WORLD - Workshop Day 1
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
