CREATED:20200116T041835Z
DESCRIPTION:Cancelled due to COVID-19: https://www.unallocatedspace.org/202
 0/03/13/covid-19-response-and-temporary-shutdown/<br><br>Our next formal Ch
 armBUG meeting will be held at Unallocated Space in Severn\, MD. The goal f
 or this meeting will be to discuss any BUG topics\, or general issues\, fol
 lowed by a talk by Ash Gokhale titled "Spi Rom Retromancy or my hardware hi
 des software that runs hardware".<br><br>There have been a lot of interesti
 ng hardware vulnerabilities and general distrust of firmware as provided by
  specific vendors in recent years. In certain cases\, vulnerabilities have 
 been found in the low level EEPROMS that have raised the questions of what 
 software is actually embedded in our hardware. Ash will be walking through 
 some interesting examples of specific hardware hacking that he has performe
 d and will share his experiences with what he found with various devices. T
 his talk will touch upon some BSD ports\, but will be a general discussion 
 of hardware hacking relevant to a general security audience.<br><br>The goa
 l will be to have an informal discussion after the talk to take questions a
 nd address any additional topics brought up by the audience members.<br><br
 >Information from Unallocated Space:<br><br>Unallocated Space (UAS) is loca
 ted at 512 Shaw Court\, Severn MD\, 21144.<br><br>Thanks go out to Unalloca
 ted Space for allowing us to host our CharmBUG meetup.<br><br>More details 
 at:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.meetup.com/CharmBUG/events/268251508/">https
 ://www.meetup.com/CharmBUG/events/268251508/</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200313T185821Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cancelled: CharmBUG Meeting - Spi Rom Retromancy
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
