DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190307T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190307T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0gbb2e02sqg0ns15bkuakjcov3@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190307T190000
CREATED:20181105T172027Z
DESCRIPTION:The Risk Management Framework (RMF) is a collection of US stand
 ards and policy with the goal of securing systems at different operating le
 vels. The idea of RMF is that one approach will not meet the requirements f
 or every system. The goal of RMF is to come to an agreement with the Accred
 iting Authorities and that is where risk is added to the RMF.\n\nGOAL: Disc
 uss system accreditation and lessons learned\n\nTHINGS TO BRING:  Questions
  and comments\n\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Junior Security Engineers\nPRESENTER: Digi
 Reign
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233423Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: The Risk with the Risk Management Framework (RMF)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
