BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190502T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190502T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0gbb2e02sqg0ns15bkuakjcov3@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190502T190000
CREATED:20181105T172027Z
DESCRIPTION:There will come a time when there are too many hard drives\, en
 dpoints\, or logs files to look at in a traditional forensic manner.\n\n\nL
 et's work on a forensic image and grab the meat'n'potatoes forensic artifac
 ts. Then we will efficiently organize and sort this data into a timeline th
 at allows for the quick conclusion of facts that will further (or pivot) ou
 r investigation. \n\n\nAll course material and and further instructions wil
 l be available at http://bit.ly/DF101\, in the DF103 subfolder. Please acqu
 ire before hand.\n\n\nGOAL: Detonate some malware and see what it does\n\nT
 HINGS TO BRING:  Windows 7+ Laptop with Powershell 5.1 (https://docs.micros
 oft.com/en-us/skypeforbusiness/set-up-your-computer-for-windows-powershell/
 download-and-install-windows-powershell-5-1) or Windows 10 version 1607+\n\
 nSKILL LEVEL:  Beginners always welcome - quick guides to scripting - no pr
 evious knowledge necessary.\n\nPRESENTER: bmack (Brian MacKenna)
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233423Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: DF-103 Efficient Forensics using Triage Tools and Sc
 ripting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
