BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200206T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200206T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0gbb2e02sqg0ns15bkuakjcov3@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200206T190000
CREATED:20181105T172027Z
DESCRIPTION:Pwn Your Growth | Life Hacks Leading to Career Advancement\n\nS
 UMMARY: When was the last time you did something new for the first time? Yo
 ur career growth requires you to be intentional. \n\nGOAL: In this presenta
 tion\, you'll gain insights on ways you\, as a female in cybersecurity\, ca
 n hack your way into a successful cyber career.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: N/A\n\n
 RELATED TOPICS:  Women In Tech\, Women in CyberSecurity\, Women in Cyber Se
 curity\, Women in Infosec\, Information Security\, Cybersecurity\, Cyber Se
 curity\, Information Technology\n\nSKILL LEVEL: 0\n\nPRESENTER: Jacquelyn B
 lanchard\n\nKEY: Buddy
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233423Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200305T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200305T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:0gbb2e02sqg0ns15bkuakjcov3@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200305T190000
CREATED:20181105T172027Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>InfoSec Night - Defending the @home like the Enterpr
 ise</strong></p><p>SUMMARY:&nbsp\;</p><p></p><p>Introduction on the way tha
 t many security personnel&nbsp\;attempts to protect the enterprise environm
 ent\, the implementation of&nbsp\;BYOD protocols and actions to ensure mobi
 le device protections. I will&nbsp\;pose the same approaches can be applied
  to the family environment. I&nbsp\;don't have any exploits this talk is mo
 re geared to protect the family&nbsp\;as we protect the enterprise. I also 
 want to display and demonstrate&nbsp\;the solutions that I have found.&nbsp
 \;</p><p>GOAL:&nbsp\;</p><p>&nbsp\;&nbsp\;I hope to demonstrate a solution 
 to the issues concerning&nbsp\;families with young humans (4-50 yrs old). H
 ow do we provide a safer&nbsp\;environment for tablets\, Internet Connectab
 le Widgets\, and doodads\,&nbsp\;when in the hands of the semi-internet sav
 vy person(s)? I will provide&nbsp\;some at cost solutions to help ease the 
 minds of parents and provide&nbsp\;reasonable control features to the house
 hold\, with minimal mental&nbsp\;overhead.&nbsp\; I will walk you through t
 he experience of being a remote&nbsp\;parent that wants to maintain communi
 cation with my children. So\, I&nbsp\;did what any security-conscious paren
 t would\, I implemented MDM&nbsp\;(mobile device management). I don’t work 
 for Google or WordPress\,&nbsp\;but I will tell you how I leveraged these p
 latforms to protect my&nbsp\;family. The technical explanation will be reas
 onable\, and you will&nbsp\;walk away understanding how you could benefit f
 rom this ideology or a&nbsp\;derivative of within your household.</p><p>I. 
 Introduction of myself and how I got here (the why)<br>II. The idea of mobi
 le device management in the enterprise (the&nbsp\;how)<br>III. What skills 
 are necessary and how I stumbled into learning&nbsp\;them<br>IV. The family
 …your greatest treasure and persistent threat&nbsp\;<br>V. Tools required&n
 bsp\;<br>VII. Calming the fears<br>a. The Kids will think I’m Watching<br>b
 . The Grandma will break it<br>c. The Dogs will eat it<br>VIII. Now it's in
 stalled on the user devices<br>a. Pros of protection<br>b. Cons of cost</p>
 <p>X. Demo&nbsp\;</p><p><br>THINGS TO BRING:&nbsp\; None</p><p>SKILL LEVEL:
  0</p><p>PRESENTER:&nbsp\;</p><p>Nico Smith (@nicolaismith1)\, DAD\, lover 
 of technology\, CPT. In U.S. Army National Guard and evangelist of Raspberr
 y Pi. I’ve been a tech hobbyist for about 12 years. Part-time Pen tester an
 d tinkerer. I have volunteered at both BSides Las Vegas and BSides DC\, I h
 ave taught intro to computing as an afterschool high school program within 
 Chicago. I Worked as both a Defensive and Offensive analyst in the private 
 sector and the military. 3 years leading Red Team engagements to support Bl
 ue Space Defenders. I love to share when I can.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233423Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:InfoSec Night - Defending the @home like the Enterprise
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
