BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190117T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190117T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190117T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: This will be the final presentation in my Red Team ser
 ies. We will briefly review material covered in Red Team 201\, then roll ri
 ght into Windows Exploitation\, Port Forwarding\, Windows Enumeration\, Cre
 dential Stealing/Reuse\, Active Directory Enumeration\, and Domain Hopping.
 \n\nGOAL: Provide attendees with intermediate understanding of exploitation
  techniques.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Computer with Kali Linux natively installe
 d or running as a VM. Be able to connect wirelessly to a closed network. No
 te taking materials.\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Individuals with basic understanding 
 of networking concepts. Topics will be explained as they are covered. Previ
 ous red team talk attendance will help\, but is not required.\n\nPRESENTER:
  nyte
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Red Teaming 203
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190221T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190221T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190221T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:Crypto mining is very lucrative when someone else is paying for
  it. Let's walk through the analysis of Windows OS artifacts and Cloud Comp
 uting data to figure out who\, what\, when\, why\, and how someone made a p
 rofit at the expense of another. Firewall rules\, Log Analysis\, internet h
 istory\, scripts...and even some Linux. We'll cover it all and how to do so
 me of this on your own as we walk through a real world based investigation.
  Basic and advanced concepts explained\, beginners welcomed and encouraged.
 \n\nGOAL: Cover wide array of technologies and forensics to draw an educate
 d and factual conclusion after bad things happen.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING:  Ques
 tions and comments\, laptop may help to follow along. All resources will be
  available at http://bit.ly/US-DF101\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone\n\nPRESENTER
 : Brian MacKenna
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC NIGHT: DF-102: Analysis of a Cryptojacking Case
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190321T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190321T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190321T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:This event will be an introduction to the Red Team/Adversary Em
 ulation tool\, Cobalt Strike. We will be covering basic functionality\, fea
 tures\, and some advanced capabilities of the program. There will be hands-
 on demonstrations for those that have demo or licensed programs.<br><br>GOA
 L: Provide high level overview of Cobalt Strike and it's functions and feat
 ures<br><br>THINGS TO BRING:&nbsp\; Students who wish to follow along hands
  on can request a trial license from https://www.cobaltstrike.com using a n
 on-free email account\, and will need to have the software installed before
  hand. Otherwise\, note taking materials will suffice.<br><br><br>SKILL LEV
 EL:&nbsp\; Everyone<br><br>PRESENTER: nyte<br><br><b>cobaltstrike.com</b><b
 r><i>Adversary Simulation and Red Team Operations Software - Cobalt Strike<
 br>Cobalt Strike is threat emulation software. Red teams and penetration te
 sters use Cobalt Strike to demonstrate the risk of a breach and evaluate ma
 ture security programs. Cobalt Strike exploits network vulnerabilities\, la
 unches spear phishing campaigns\, hosts web drive-by attacks\, and generate
 s malware infected files from a powerful graphical user interface that enco
 urages collaboration and reports all activity.</i>
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Intro to Cobalt Strike
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
