DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190418T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190418T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: We will cover the basic concepts of Virtual Private Ne
 tworking technology including types\, use cases\, and options for setting u
 p your own.\n\nGOAL: Understand what using a VPN means and why you might wa
 nt to use one.\n\nSKILL LEVEL: Everyone\n\nPRESENTER: BobbyR
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: VPN Explained
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190516T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190516T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190516T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:This presentation will be an introduction to web app pen testin
 g\; specifically how to use Burp and Zap. These programs are commonly used 
 during web penetration assessments\, web app testing\, and can even be used
  in mobile app testing. We will go over some basics of web site functions\,
  cover basic functionality of the tools\, and provide some practice website
 s to tinker with.\n\nGOAL: Provide an introductory understanding of web app
 lication testing\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Note taking material\, laptop with Bur
 p and/or Zap installed (or a Kali Linux distro)\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone. 
 Basic understanding of web technologies is helpful but will be covered duri
 ng the presentation\n\nPRESENTER: nyte
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Introduction to Web App Pen Testing using Burp and Z
 ap
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190620T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190620T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190620T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: An intro into digital forensics\, from legal concepts 
 and chain of custody\, to forensic imaging and artifacts. High level overvi
 ews of concepts for beginners and those interested in the field. \n\n\nGOAL
 : Basic understanding of digital forensics from start to finish.\nTHINGS TO
  BRING: Questions and Comments   \n\n\nLEVEL:  Everyone\n\nPRESENTER: Brian
  MacKenna
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC Night: Digital Forensics 101
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190718T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190718T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190718T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:This presentation will cover some basic ideas to exploit firmwa
 re. We will be discussing basics of firmware\, acquiring firmware\, extract
 ion\, analysis\, and (if time allows) backdooring firmware. Hands-on exampl
 es for extraction and analysis will be conducted. Basic concepts\, such as 
 Linux file structure and tools\, will be covered.\n\nGOAL: Extract and anal
 yze firmware for exploitation/bug hunting.\n\nTHINGS TO BRING: Note taking 
 material. If wanting to follow along with the exercise\, bring a laptop wit
 h your favorite version of Linux installed. Download the following tools ah
 ead of time - Binwalk (https://github.com/ReFirmLabs/binwalk)\, Firmware Mo
 d Kit (https://github.com/rampageX/firmware-mod-kit/wiki)\, Firmware Analys
 is Toolkit (https://github.com/attify/firmware-analysis-toolkit)\, Firmwalk
 er (https://github.com/craigz28/firmwalker)\, and qemu (from your distro re
 pository)\n\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Everyone\nPRESENTER: Nyte
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:INFOSEC NIGHT: Intro to Firmware Exploitation
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20190815T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20190815T210000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20190815T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:Less talk\, more rock. CFREDS.nist.gov has a prepackage forensi
 cs scenario with questions and answers. Let's treat this like a real case -
  talk about chain of custody\, notes\, timelines\, and find the answers to 
 the questions provided. Case materials available at https://www.cfreds.nist
 .gov/data_leakage_case/data-leakage-case.html. Further resources and materi
 als to be provided at: http://bit.ly/US-DF101 - folder DF104.\n\n\nGOAL: Fi
 nd forensic artifacts and information pertinent to an investigation.\n\nTHI
 NGS TO BRING:  Laptop or VM with Windows OS with plenty free space (20+ GB)
 . Please check the DF104 (bit.ly/US-DF101) folder for further instructions\
 , software\, etc.\n\nSKILL LEVEL:  Beginners welcome\, but Intermediate and
  familiarity with forensics recommended.\n\nPRESENTER: Brian MacKenna / bma
 ck
