DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200319T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200319T220000
DTSTAMP:20250626T025311Z
UID:2bdii5cilt5su88r1gd4pk9urp@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200319T190000
CREATED:20181105T172435Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Cancelled due to COVID-19: https://www.unallocatedspace.org/
 2020/03/13/covid-19-response-and-temporary-shutdown/<strong><br></strong></
 p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p><strong>InfoSec Night - Zeek 3.0 Network S
 ecurity Monitor &amp\; Me</strong></p><p>SUMMARY: An interactive Zeek 3.0 p
 resentation with audience participation! What is Zeek (Bro IDS)? Zeek\, for
 merly known as Bro\, is an open-source software framework for analyzing net
 work traffic that is most commonly used to detect behavioral anomalies on a
  network for cybersecurity purposes. Zeek provides capabilities that are si
 milar to network intrusion detection systems (IDS)\, however\, thinking abo
 ut Zeek exclusively as an IDS doesn’t effectively describe the breadth of i
 ts capabilities. This is because Zeek enables security operations centers (
 SOC) to do much more – including performing incident response\, forensics\,
  file extraction\, and hashing among other capabilities.</p><p>THINGS TO BR
 ING: Laptop</p><p>SKILL LEVEL: 0</p><p>PRESENTER: Chuck</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233452Z
