 meetup exists to support a hands on approach for beginners who want to lear
 n about pin and tumbler lock-picking. Veteran pickers who want to discuss m
 ore advanced topics like security pins\, different locking mechanisms\, key
  impressioning\, decoding\, and safe manipulation are all welcome\, but the
 re is an Advanced lockpicking night as well.\n\nFormat \nTypically we cover
  a primer on the single pin picking (SPP) of pin and tumbler locks over the
  course of 15 minutes. Then spend about 35-40 doing hands on picking togeth
 er before moving back to class-wide Q&A briefly. Then we spend the rest of 
 the time picking and sharing advice. The 15 minutes of the presentation is 
 formal\, the rest is casual. \n\n\nEquipment \nIf you have lockpicks or loc
 ks you’re encouraged to bring them. We do sell introductory kits and have a
  set of beginner locks and picks anyone can use. \n\n\nInstructor Note \nHe
 y I’m Flay. I’ve been lockpicking for years and was the 2 time winner of th
 e GrrCon ‘Cage of shame’ lockpicking challenge. I think its great fun\, and
  I’m excited to be able to encourage others in the hobby. Its my goal to en
 sure that everyone who comes to the meetup walks away having picked at leas
 t one lock and that all the veterans learn something from each other.
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233505Z
