RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20200408T190000
CREATED:20171216T230211Z
DESCRIPTION:Purpose \nCurrently our meetup exists to support a hands on app
 roach for beginners who want to learn about pin and tumbler lock-picking. V
 eteran pickers who want to discuss more advanced topics like security pins\
 , different locking mechanisms\, key impressioning\, decoding\, and safe ma
 nipulation are all welcome\, but there is an Advanced lockpicking night as 
 well.\n\nFormat \nTypically we cover a primer on the single pin picking (SP
 P) of pin and tumbler locks over the course of 15 minutes. Then spend about
  35-40 doing hands on picking together before moving back to class-wide Q&A
  briefly. Then we spend the rest of the time picking and sharing advice. Th
 e 15 minutes of the presentation is formal\, the rest is casual. \n\n\nEqui
 pment \nIf you have lockpicks or locks you’re encouraged to bring them. We 
 do sell introductory kits and have a set of beginner locks and picks anyone
  can use. \n\n\nInstructor Note \nHey I’m Flay. I’ve been lockpicking for y
 ears and was the 2 time winner of the GrrCon ‘Cage of shame’ lockpicking ch
 allenge. I think its great fun\, and I’m excited to be able to encourage ot
 hers in the hobby. Its my goal to ensure that everyone who comes to the mee
 tup walks away having picked at least one lock and that all the veterans le
 arn something from each other.
LAST-MODIFIED:20201022T233505Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct #105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
