DESCRIPTION:&nbsp\;<strong>Maryland Meltdown</strong><p>SUMMARY: Maryland A
 rea Combat Robotics (MACRO) is hosting a 3d printed plastic ant weight (1 p
 ound) robot combat event</p><p></p><p>GOAL: To increase participation in ro
 botic combat sports\, by lowering the financial barrier to entry. To help p
 articipants learn engineering\, material science\, 3d modeling\, 3d printin
 g\, remote control systems and good sportsmanship\, which all contribute to
  the enjoyment of robotic combat sports.</p><p></p><p>THINGS TO BRING: One 
 or more 3d printed combat robots\, which adhere to the construction rules l
 aid out&nbsp\;<a href="http://macrobot.us/MACRO_Robot_Construction_Specific
 ations_v2021-03-25.pdf">here</a>. There are a limited number of slots avail
 able\, so please register at&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.robotcombatevents.c
 om/events/605">robotcombatevents.com</a>&nbsp\;</p><p></p><p>SKILL LEVEL: B
 eginner to Expert.&nbsp\; We welcome all participants!</p><p></p><p>PRESENT
 ER: Maryland Area Combat Robotics (MACRO)</p><p>FEE: $15 per combat robot</
 p><p>KEYHOLDER: Bowie/James</p><p></p><p>If you have questions\, we have an
  active Discord server.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<a href="https://discord.gg/SXwArmv">h
 ttps://discord.gg/<wbr>SXwArmv</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210415T230350Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Maryland Meltdown
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
