DESCRIPTION:SUMMARY: Maryland Area Combat Robotics (MACRO) is hosting a 3d 
 printed plastic ant weight (1 pound) robot combat test and tune event\, whe
 re people can test their robots in a safe and controlled environment.<br><b
 r>GOAL: To increase participation in robotic combat sports\, by lowering th
 e financial barrier to entry. To help participants learn engineering\, mate
 rial science\, 3d modeling\, 3d printing\, remote control systems and good 
 sportsmanship\, which all contribute to the enjoyment of robotic combat spo
 rts.<br><br>THINGS TO BRING: One or more 3d printed combat robots\, which a
 dhere to the construction rules laid out at herehttp://<a href="http://macr
 obot.us/construction-specifications/"><u>macrobot.us/construction-specifica
 tions/</u></a> . If you have questions regarding the rules\, please feel fr
 ee to join us on our <a href="https://discord.gg/SXwArmv"><u>Discord</u></a
 >&nbsp\;or email us at "officer@macrobot.us".  Questions are answered very 
 quickly by our staff. There are a limited number of slots available\, so pl
 ease register at <a href="https://www.robotcombatevents.com/events/748"><u>
 robotcombatevents.com&nbsp\;</u></a><br><br>SKILL LEVEL: Beginner to Expert
 .  We welcome all participants!<br><br>PRESENTER: Maryland Area Combat Robo
 tics (MACRO)<br><br>Keyholder: Ty McNeer/Jeff Story
