DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>SUMMARY: Maryland Area Combat Robotics (MACRO) is
  hosting a 3d<br>printed plastic ant weight (1 pound) and full combat ant w
 eight (1 pound) robot combat event</p><p>GOAL:&nbsp\;To increase participat
 ion in robotic combat sports\, by<br>lowering the financial barrier to entr
 y. To help participants learn<br>engineering\, material science\, 3d modeli
 ng\, 3d printing\, remote control systems<br>and good sportsmanship\, which
  all contribute to the enjoyment of robotic combat<br>sports.</p><p></p><p>
 THINGS TO BRING:&nbsp\;One or more 3d printed combat robots\, which adhere 
 to the<br>construction rules laid out at&nbsp\;<a href="http://http2F2Fcons
 truction-specifications/">http://macrobot.us/construc<u></u>tion-specificat
 ions/</a>&nbsp\;.<br>If you have questions regarding the rules\, please fee
 l free to join us on our<br>Discord&nbsp\;<a href="http://https2F2FSXwArmv"
 >https://discord.gg/SXw<u></u>Armv</a>&nbsp\;or email<br>"<a href="mailto:o
 fficer@macrobot.us">officer@macrobot.us</a>". Questions are answered very q
 uickly by<br>our staff. There are a limited number of slots available\, so 
 please register<br>at&nbsp\;<a href="http://https2F2Fevents/749">https://ww
 w.robotcombateven<u></u>ts.com/</a></p><p>SKILL LEVEL:&nbsp\;Beginner to Ex
 pert. We welcome all participants!</p><p></p><p></p><p>PRESENTER:&nbsp\;Mar
 yland Area Combat Robotics (MACRO) Live<br>Stream:&nbsp\;<a href="https://w
 ww.youtube.com/channel/UCK5J7oVaIkWkhP8eDAGOxrA">https://www.youtube.co<u><
 /u>m/channel/UCK5J7oVaIkWkhP8eDAG<u></u>OxrA</a></p></html-blob>
