CREATED:20220725T224333Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p><b><b>Course Description:&nbsp\;</b></b>​This pro
 gressive\, hands-on course will cover the fundamentals of electronics\, inc
 luding direct current (DC)\, alternating current (AC)\, and semiconductors.
  As we progress though the course we’ll build and analyze a variable DC pow
 er supply\, then build an audio amplifier.</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Instructo
 r:</b> Corey Koval (<a href="mailto:corey@unallocatedspace.org">corey@unall
 ocatedspace.org</a>)</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><b><b>Required Materials:</b></b><
 /p><ul><li>Notebook</li><li>Pen/Pencils</li><li>Scientific Calculator</li><
 li>Variable DC power supply:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.circuitspecialists.
 com/csi1501.html">https://www.circuitspecialists.com/csi1501.html</a></li><
 li>Resistor assortment:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10
 969">https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10969</a></li><li>Digital Multimeter
 :&nbsp\;<a href="http://www.circuitspecialists.com/digital-multimeter-csi20
 10.html">http://www.circuitspecialists.com/digital-multimeter-csi2010.html<
 /a></li><li>Breadboard&nbsp\;<a href="http://www.circuitspecialists.com/wb-
 102+j.html">http://www.circuitspecialists.com/wb-102+j.html</a></li><li>jum
 per wires (with and without alligator clips)&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.cir
 cuitspecialists.com/m000f0002.html">https://www.circuitspecialists.com/m000
 f0002.html</a></li><li>Magnifying glass if you need one to see up close</li
 ></ul><p>&nbsp\;</p><p><b><b>Course Outline</b></b></p><p><b><b>Topic #1: D
 C:</b></b>&nbsp\;​definitions\, voltage\, current\, electrons\, how electro
 ns flow\, Ohm’s law\, resistors\, resistor color code\, resistor dividers\,
  series circuits\, parallel circuits\, series-parallel circuits\, power\, d
 iodes\, switches and circuit protection\, capacitors\, inductors</p><p><b><
 b>Topic #2: AC:&nbsp\;</b></b>​frequency\, waveforms\, capacitors\, capacit
 ive reactance\, inductors\, inductive reactance\, impedance\, RLC circuits\
 , transformers\, rectifiers\, voltage regulators</p><p><b><b>Topic #3:&nbsp
 \;</b></b>Semiconductors: ​transistors\, amplifiers</p></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221029T132629Z
LOCATION:Unallocated Space\, 512 Shaw Ct Suite 105\, Severn\, MD 21144\, US
 A
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Electronics Fundamentals
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
