DESCRIPTION:Hello Unallocated Space Members\,<br><br>We are on our way to a
  new normal. Vaccines are being distributed\, infection and hospitalization
  rates are down\, and COVID restrictions in the county are being lifted.<br
 ><br>As we return to a new normal we are hosting a town hall on Sunday\, Ju
 ne 13th from 11am to 12:30pm. This townhall is to focus on engaging with ou
 r members to discuss our COVID guidelines\, find people willing to teach or
  host events\, and to talk about how you’d like to see the space in 2021-20
 22. To put it another way\, how would you like to participate and see Unall
 ocated Space in our new normal.<br><br>These questions are not easily answe
 red. We would like to encourage anyone who wants to participate in this dis
 cussion and those who would like to bring up other topics\, please feel fre
 e to participate.<br><br>This will be a VIRTUAL town hall to keep it simple
 .&nbsp\;<a href="https://zoom.us/j/94652449197?pwd=ZjRNOFZLTFlnV0l0U2dMRUts
 OXV0Zz09">Click here to join over Zoom</a>&nbsp\;or use the meeting id "946
  5244 9197" with a passcode of "545879".<br><br>Also\, we do have a survey 
 to help gather information about our members preferences before the town ha
 ll. If you have time please fill it out at&nbsp\;<a href="https://forms.gle
 /tkARPwZU3uEojwMH8">https://forms.gle/<wbr>tkARPwZU3uEojwMH8</a>.<br><br>In
  the meantime\, please feel free to reach out&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:board@u
 nallocatedspace.org">board@unallocatedspace.org</a>&nbsp\;if you have any q
 uestions\, comments\, or concerns.<br><br>My Best\,
LAST-MODIFIED:20230307T092027Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UAS Town Hall
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
