UID:466mgj8rgu3p2ssj2mctt8voaj@google.com
CREATED:20240209T151434Z
DESCRIPTION:Come to Unallocated's very first Arts and Crafts Swap Meet!<br>
 <br>Summary: Have you ever started a craft project and ran out of steam bef
 ore you finished? Or got stuff on a whim and don't know what to do with it?
  Do you have a box of supplies in a corner haunting you like a beating hear
 t under the floorboards? Bring them to Unallocated!<br><br>Goal: Spring cle
 an your crafts. Meet other crafters and creatives and discuss all those pro
 jects that were not meant to be. Pick up supplies for those projects that A
 RE meant to be! The goal is to get supplies you don't need out of your home
  and into the hands of people who could use them and get supplies you do ne
 ed onto your craft table. Maybe you'll find a new hobby!<br><br>Things to B
 ring: All sorts of craft stuff you can do without! Paints\, yarn\, fabric\,
  scrapbooking supplies\, beads\, embroidery kits... you name it! Bring it a
 ll! We will help sort it and get it to people who can use it instead of hav
 ing it take up space in your home.<br><br>Skill Level: Everyone is welcome!
  Whether you are brand new to making things or are a craftier extraordinair
 e\, we hope you'll find something at this event.<br><br>Presenters: Thea an
 d Whitney<br><p>Don't want to take unclaimed supplies back home? We will be
  donating leftover items to Aunt Hazel's Witchcraft Project\, LLC. They are
  a pay-as-you-can craft supply store and maker space in Lauraville.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240209T151511Z
LOCATION:512 Shaw Ct\, Severn\, MD 21144\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arts and Crafts Swap Meet
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
