DESCRIPTION:<span><br><p><strong>Embedded programming from level 0 using th
 e stm32 “blackpill” mcu</strong></p><p><strong>SUMMARY</strong>: What does 
 learning about embedded systems and reverse engineering take? We discuss th
 e challenges involved in installing Ghidra and making STM32 boards blink\, 
 from ditching the Arduino IDE to working through ssh\, reading endless page
 s of datasheets to learning about registers\, we delve deeper into the embe
 dded world.</p><p><strong>GOAL</strong>: Emphasize the challenges of starti
 ng with embedded programming from level 0 and how we overcame them.</p><p><
 strong>THINGS TO BRING</strong>: A smile.</p><p><strong>SKILL LEVEL</strong
 >: Beginner</p><p><strong>PRESENTER</strong>: Evan and Adrian</p></span>
