DESCRIPTION:<p><span>Due to Charm City Lego User Group's bylaws\, you must 
 be over 18 to attend or join.<br></span><span><br></span></p><p><span>Charm
  City LUG is made up of over 50 AFOL (Adult Fans of LEGO®) members from Bal
 timore\, Maryland and its surrounding area. We are spread across a wide ran
 ge of ages\, backgrounds\, and professions\, but all share the same love of
  LEGO. Some of our members have over 30 years of building experience with L
 EGO\, while others have newly discovered the hobby. Similarly some members 
 enjoy the collecting aspect of the hobby or building official sets\, while 
 others focus their energy on building original creations\, commonly referre
 d to a MOC (My Own Creation). All of these interests are welcome\, and enco
 uraged. Our diversity is our strength and contributes to the wealth of know
 ledge and experiences that we share among our membership. We welcome all LE
 GO enthusiasts\, from all backgrounds\, to participate in our events and ac
 tivities. Similarly we invite those within community who are 18 and older t
 o consider joining us as a formal member of the LUG.</span></p><p>During th
 ese meetings\, we hold themed build challenges\, discuss recent set reviews
  and LEGO news\, and hold presentations from members highlighting interesti
 ng build techniques and projects they are working on. In addition\, we use 
 these meetings to discuss and plan for upcoming public events and shows all
  around the region and nation in which the LUG is represented by member bui
 lders showing off their work.</p><p>Outside of monthly meetings\, members m
 eet for sorting parties\, collaborative build projects\, public and private
  build events\, and general socialization. </p><p>You can check out our upc
 oming meetings and events on the Charm City LUG website.<br><br><a href="ht
 tps://www.charmcitylug.com/" target="_blank">https://www.charmcitylug.com/<
 /a></p>
