 ></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Stitching a quilt together</span
 ></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Binding</span></p></li><li dir="
 ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Activity: Potholder/Hot Pad: Choose Your Own Advent
 ure!</span></p></li></ul><p></p><p dir="ltr"><span>Missed Lessons 1 and 2? 
 No worries! You can join us for Lesson 3 if you have a basic understanding 
 of how a sewing machine works and how to sew straight lines.</span></p><p><
 /p><p dir="ltr"><span><b>THINGS TO BRING:</b></span></p><ul><li dir="ltr"><
 p dir="ltr"><span>Sewing machine</span></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">
 <span>At least three fat quarters of quilting cotton</span></p></li><li dir
 ="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Two 8”x8” pieces of quilt batting (preferably cot
 ton)</span></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Matching thread</span>
 </p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>One package of double fold bias t
 ape</span></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Scissors or a rotary bl
 ade and mat</span></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Straight pins</
 span></p></li><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr"><span>Ruler or measuring tape</spa
 n></p></li></ul><p></p><p dir="ltr"><span>We have limited supplies for this
  class. If you would like to use our supplies\, please consider making a sm
